2713 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_PROC && argcnt == 5 &&
2714 strcmp(SYMNAME(sptr), mkRteRtnNm(RTE_instance)) == 0) {
2715 int stdprev, astprev;
2716 stdprev = STD_PREV(std);
2717 astprev = STD_AST(stdprev);
2718 if (A_TYPEG(astprev) == A_CALL) {
2719 int sptrprev, set_intrin_type_std = 0;
2720 sptrprev = A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(astprev));
2721 if (STYPEG(sptrprev) == ST_PROC &&
2722 strcmp(SYMNAME(sptrprev), mkRteRtnNm(RTE_set_intrin_type)) == 0) {
2723 int stdtmp, asttmp;
2724 stdtmp = STD_PREV(stdprev);
2725 asttmp = STD_AST(stdtmp);
2726 if (A_TYPEG(asttmp) == A_CALL) {
2727 int sptrtmp = A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(asttmp));
2728 if (STYPEG(sptrtmp) == ST_PROC &&
2729 strcmp(SYMNAME(sptrtmp), mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template)) == 0) {
2730 set_intrin_type_std = stdprev;
2731 stdprev = stdtmp;
2732 astprev = asttmp;
2733 sptrprev = sptrtmp;
2734 }
2735 }
2736 }
2737 if (STYPEG(sptrprev) == ST_PROC &&
2738 strcmp(SYMNAME(sptrprev), mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template)) == 0) {
2739 /* get argument lists */
2740 int argsi, insd, outsd, argst, tempsd, sptrsd, collapse;
2741 argsi = A_ARGSG(ast);
2742 outsd = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 0);
2743 insd = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 1);
2744 argst = A_ARGSG(astprev);
2745 tempsd = ARGT_ARG(argst, 0);
2746 sptrsd = sym_of_ast(tempsd);
2747 collapse = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 4);
2748 if (sptrsd && !VISITG(sptrsd) && tempsd == insd &&
2749 tempsd != outsd) {
2750 if (collapse == astb.i0 || collapse == astb.k0) {
2751 /* replace
2752 * call RTE_template(aa$sd,1,2,0,0,1,20)
2753 * call pghpf_instance(aa$sd1,aa$sd,27,4,0)
2754 * by
2755 * call RTE_template(aa$sd1,1,2,27,4,1,20)
2756 */
2757 ARGT_ARG(argst, 0) = outsd;
2758 ARGT_ARG(argst, 3) = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 2);
2759 ARGT_ARG(argst, 4) = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 3);
2760 delete_stmt(std);
2761 if (set_intrin_type_std != 0)
2762 delete_stmt(set_intrin_type_std);
2763 } else {
2764 /* replace
2765 * call RTE_template(aa$sd,1,2,0,0,1,20)
2766 * call pghpf_instance(aa$sd1,aa$sd,27,4,0)
2767 * by
2768 * call RTE_template(aa$sd1,1,2,0,0,1,20)
2769 * call pghpf_instance(aa$sd1,aa$sd1,27,4,0)
2770 */
2771 ARGT_ARG(argsi, 1) = outsd;
2772 ARGT_ARG(argst, 0) = outsd;
2773 }
2774 STYPEP(sptrsd, ST_UNKNOWN);
2775 }
2776 if (sptrsd && tempsd == insd && tempsd == outsd &&
2777 (collapse == astb.i0 || collapse == astb.k0)) {
2778 /* replace
2779 * call RTE_template(aa$sd,1,2,0,0,1,20)
2780 * call pghpf_instance(aa$sd,aa$sd,27,4,0)
2781 * by
2782 * call RTE_template(aa$sd,1,2,27,4,1,20)
2783 */
2784 ARGT_ARG(argst, 3) = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 2);
2785 ARGT_ARG(argst, 4) = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 3);
2786 delete_stmt(std);
2787 if (set_intrin_type_std != 0)
2788 delete_stmt(set_intrin_type_std);
2789 }
2790 }
2791 }
2792 }
2793 }
2794 }
2795
2796 /* go back and reset VISIT flags again */
2797 for (sptr = stb.firstosym; sptr < stb.stg_avail; ++sptr) {
2798 VISITP(sptr, 0);
2799 }
2800
2801 /* look for pghpf_instance calls where the input/output descriptors
2802 * are identical; replace by assignments
2803 * look for RTE_template calls;
2804 * if the rank is constant, replace by
2805 * RTE_template1/RTE_template2/RTE_template3 or
2806 * RTE_template1v/RTE_template2v/RTE_template3v calls, as appropriate */
2807 for (std = STD_NEXT(0); std; std = stdnext) {
2808 int ast, sptr, argcnt;
2809 stdnext = STD_NEXT(std);
2810 ast = STD_AST(std);
2811 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_CALL) {
2812 sptr = memsym_of_ast(A_LOPG(ast));
2813 argcnt = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
2814 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_PROC && argcnt == 5 &&
2815 strcmp(SYMNAME(sptr), mkRteRtnNm(RTE_instance)) == 0) {
2816 /* replace call pghpf_instance(a$sd,a$sd,kind,len,0)
2817 * by direct assignment
2818 * a$sd(kindoffset) = kind
2819 * a$sd(lenoffset) = len
2820 */
2821 int argsi, outsd, insd, collapse;
2822 argsi = A_ARGSG(ast);
2823 outsd = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 0);
2824 insd = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 1);
2825 collapse = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 4);
2826 if (outsd == insd && A_TYPEG(insd) == A_ID &&
2827 (collapse == astb.i0 || collapse == astb.k0)) {
2828 int kind, len, lhs, newasn, newstd;
2829 insd = A_SPTRG(insd);
2830 kind = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 2);
2831 len = ARGT_ARG(argsi, 3);
2832 lhs = get_kind(insd);
2833 newasn = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
2834 A_DESTP(newasn, lhs);
2835 A_SRCP(newasn, kind);
2836 newstd = add_stmt_before(newasn, std);
2837 lhs = get_byte_len(insd);
2838 newasn = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
2839 A_DESTP(newasn, lhs);
2840 A_SRCP(newasn, len);
2841 STD_AST(std) = newasn;
2842 }
2843 } else if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_PROC &&
2844 strcmp(SYMNAME(sptr), mkRteRtnNm(RTE_template)) == 0) {
2845 /* call RTE_template(aa$sd,rank,flags,kind,len,lb1,lb2)
2846 * turn into
2847 * call RTE_template1(aa$sd,flags,kind,len,lb1,lb2) */
2848 int args, rank, ii;
2849 args = A_ARGSG(ast);
2850 rank = ARGT_ARG(args, 1);
2851 if (A_ALIASG(rank)) {
2852 rank = A_ALIASG(rank);
2853 rank = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(rank));
2854 if (rank >= 1 && rank <= 3) {
2855 int fsptr, a;
2856 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn;
2857 /* one fewer argument */
2858 --argcnt;
2859 for (a = 1; a < argcnt; ++a) {
2860 ARGT_ARG(args, a) = ARGT_ARG(args, a + 1);
2861 }
2862 ARGT_CNT(args) = argcnt;
2863 A_ARGCNTP(ast, argcnt);
2864 if (size_of(DT_PTR) != size_of(DT_INT)) {
2865 /* on hammer, seems faster to pass by ref */
2866 switch (rank) {
2867 case 1:
2868 rtlRtn = RTE_template1;
2869 break;
2870 case 2:
2871 rtlRtn = RTE_template2;
2872 break;
2873 case 3:
2874 rtlRtn = RTE_template3;
2875 break;
2876 }
2877 } else {
2878 switch (rank) {
2879 case 1:
2880 rtlRtn = RTE_template1v;
2881 break;
2882 case 2:
2883 rtlRtn = RTE_template2v;
2884 break;
2885 case 3:
2886 rtlRtn = RTE_template3v;
2887 break;
2888 }
2889 for (a = 1; a < argcnt; ++a) {
2890 ARGT_ARG(args, a) = mk_unop(OP_VAL, ARGT_ARG(args, a), DT_INT);
2891 }
2892 }
2893 fsptr = sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), DT_NONE);
2894 NODESCP(fsptr, 1);
2895 ii = mk_id(fsptr);
2896 A_LOPP(ast, ii);
2897 /*
2898 * tpr 3569: a call to RTE_template() without the
2899 * upperbound of the last dimension is generated
2900 * for an assumed-size array. But, the rank-specific
2901 * template functions accesses the upper bound
2902 * which could cause a segfault. Just add the
2903 * the dimension's lowerbound as the upper bound.
2904 */
2905 if (argcnt < rank * 2 + 4) {
2906 ARGT_ARG(args, argcnt) = ARGT_ARG(args, argcnt - 1);
2907 argcnt++;
2908 ARGT_CNT(args) = argcnt;
2909 A_ARGCNTP(ast, argcnt);
2910 }
2911 }
2912 }
2913 }
2914 }
2915 }
2916} /* convert_template_instance */
2917
2918static int
2919conv_deallocate(int std)
2920{
2921 int dealloc_ast, idast;
2922 int ast;
2923 int sptr = 0;
2924 int argt;
2925 int secd;
2926 int arrdsc;
2927 LITEMF *list;
2928 int i;
2929 int nargs;
2930
2931 dealloc_ast = A_SRCG(STD_AST(std));
2932again:
2933 switch (A_TYPEG(dealloc_ast)) {
2934 case A_ID:
2935 sptr = A_SPTRG(dealloc_ast);
2936 idast = dealloc_ast;
2937 break;
2938 case A_MEM:
2939 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(dealloc_ast));
2940 idast = dealloc_ast;
2941 break;
2942 case A_SUBSCR:
2943 dealloc_ast = A_LOPG(dealloc_ast);
2944 goto again;
2945 default:
2946 interr("conv_deallocate: unexpected ast", dealloc_ast, 4);
2947 }
2948
2949 /* free the section and the align */
2950 arrdsc = DESCRG(sptr);
2951 if (arrdsc == 0)
2952 goto exit_;
2953 secd = SECDG(arrdsc);
2954 if (secd == 0)
2955 goto exit_;
2956
2957 list = 0;
2958 for (i = 0; i < tbl.avl; i++) {
2959 if (tbl.base[i].f1 == sptr)
2960 list = tbl.base[i].f3;
2961 else if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER && STYPEG(tbl.base[i].f1) == ST_MEMBER &&
2962 ENCLDTYPEG(sptr) == ENCLDTYPEG(tbl.base[i].f1) &&
2963 strcmp(SYMNAME(sptr), SYMNAME(tbl.base[i].f1)) == 0) {
2964 /* This occurs with parameterized derived types */
2965 list = tbl.base[i].f3;
2966 }
2967 }
2968
2969 /*
2970 * f22379: there are cases where 'all' descriptors are created where there
2971 * may not be a matching allocate, such as a a pointer member of a
2972 * polymorphic typ> For now, I'm just removing the assert for now -- in the
2973 * future, we may want to qualify the assert.
2974 assert(list, "conv_deallocate: did not find corresponding allocate", sptr, 3);
2975 */
2976 if (!list || list->nitem == 0)
2977 goto exit_;
2978 nargs = list->nitem + 1;
2979 argt = mk_argt(nargs);
2980 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = mk_cval(list->nitem, DT_INT);
2981 for (i = 0; i < list->nitem; i++) {
2982 int mast;
2983 mast = check_member(idast, mk_id(glist(list, i)));
2984 ARGT_ARG(argt, list->nitem - i) = mast;
2985 }
2986 ast = mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(sym_mkfunc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_freen), DT_NONE)),
2987 nargs, argt);
2988 add_stmt_before(ast, std);
2989exit_:
2990 std = STD_NEXT(std);
2991 if (STD_IGNORE(STD_PREV(std)))
2992 delete_stmt(STD_PREV(std));
2993 return std;
2994}
2995
2996/* Algorithm:
2997 * This routine converts allocatable arrays.
2998 * allocate(a(a$sd(33):a$sd(34)))
2999 * This allocate stmt is user defined statement
3000 * not compiler define allocates.
3001 * It calls emit_alnd_secd to set align and section descriptor
3002 * for allocatable arrays.
3003 * emit_alnd_secd has to generate algn and sec just before allocate stmt
3004 * unlike non-array.
3005 */
3006extern LOGICAL want_descriptor_anyway(int sptr);
3007
3008static int
3009conv_allocate(int std)
3010{
3011 int alloc_ast, idast;
3012 int sptr = 0;
3013 int subsc, memast;
3014 int i;
3015 int asd;
3016 int dtype;
3017 int align;
3018 LITEMF *list;
3019 int nd;
3020 int a_dtype;
3021
3022 alloc_ast = STD_AST(std);
3023 memast = subsc = A_SRCG(alloc_ast);
3024 /* only set a_dtype for typed allocation, not sourced allocation, etc. */
3025 a_dtype = (!A_STARTG(alloc_ast)) ? A_DTYPEG(alloc_ast) : 0;
3026 switch (A_TYPEG(subsc)) {
3027 case A_SUBSCR:
3028 sptr = sptr_of_subscript(subsc);
3029 memast = idast = A_LOPG(subsc);
3030 asd = A_ASDG(subsc);
3031 if (!HCCSYMG(sptr)) {
3032 /* if the sptr is not a compiler generated temp, skip the "UGLY HACK"
3033 * This became necessary with the addition of ALLOCATE SOURCE/MOLD.
3034 * TODO: Think this needs to be revisited.
3035 */
3036 break;
3037 }
3038 /* UGLY HACK:
3039 * if this is a temporary that was created on behalf of
3040 * a derived type member, use the member as the 'idast' */
3041 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
3042 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
3043 int lower = ADD_LWBD(dtype, 0);
3044 if (lower && A_TYPEG(lower) == A_SUBSCR)
3045 lower = A_LOPG(lower);
3046 if (lower && A_TYPEG(lower) == A_MEM) {
3047 idast = lower;
3048 } else if (lower && A_TYPEG(lower) == A_ID &&
3049 STYPEG(A_SPTRG(lower)) == ST_MEMBER) {
3050 /* candidate case */
3051 int subs;
3052 subs = ASD_SUBS(asd, 0);
3053 if (subs && A_TYPEG(subs) == A_TRIPLE)
3054 subs = A_LBDG(subs);
3055 if (subs && A_TYPEG(subs) == A_SUBSCR)
3056 subs = A_LOPG(subs);
3057 if (subs && A_TYPEG(subs) == A_MEM)
3058 idast = subs;
3059 }
3060 }
3061 break;
3062 case A_ID:
3063 sptr = A_SPTRG(subsc);
3064 idast = subsc;
3065 subsc = 0;
3066 break;
3067 case A_MEM:
3068 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(subsc));
3069 idast = subsc;
3070 subsc = 0;
3071 break;
3072 default:
3073 interr("conv_allocate: unexpected ast", alloc_ast, 4);
3074 }
3075
3076 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) != TY_ARRAY)
3077 goto exit_;
3078 /* pointer based but not allocatable variables */
3079 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED && !ALLOCG(sptr))
3080 goto exit_;
3081 if (NODESCG(sptr))
3082 goto exit_;
3083
3084 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
3085 /* put out the array bounds assignments */
3086
3087 align = ALIGNG(sptr);
3088 if (want_descriptor_anyway(sptr))
3089 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
3090
3091 init_fl();
3092
3093 /* if this is a host subprogram, it
3094 * may be passed as argument in a contained subprogram,
3095 * but we don't know here */
3096 if (gbl.internal == 1 || STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER)
3097 DESCUSEDP(sptr, 1);
3098 if (DESCUSEDG(sptr) && !TPALLOCG(sptr)) {
3099 set_typed_alloc(a_dtype);
3100 emit_alnd_secd(sptr, idast, TRUE, std, subsc);
3101 set_typed_alloc(DT_NONE);
3102 }
3103
3104 /* allocating an array pointer, need to plug the runtime desc gbase field */
3105 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_ARRAY && POINTERG(sptr) &&
3106 (flg.debug || XBIT(70, 0x2000000))) {
3107 int src;
3108 int dest;
3109 int stmt;
3110 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
3111 src = mk_member(A_PARENTG(idast), mk_id(MIDNUMG(sptr)),
3112 DTYPEG(MIDNUMG(sptr)));
3113 dest = check_member(idast, get_gbase(SDSCG(sptr)));
3114 } else {
3115 src = mk_id(MIDNUMG(sptr));
3116 dest = get_gbase(SDSCG(sptr));
3117 }
3118 /*
3119 * For the time being, the pointer is copied to the gbase field
3120 * by the runtime routine, RTE_ptrcp(). This has always been the
3121 * behavior for 64-bit; however, for 32-bit, we were generating
3122 * assignments. Unfortuately, there is an ili mismatch (the
3123 * source is 'AR' and the store expects 'IR') caught by dump_ili().
3124 */
3125 stmt = begin_call(A_CALL, sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_ptrcp), DT_NONE),
3126 2);
3127 add_arg(dest);
3128 add_arg(src);
3129
3130 add_stmt_after(stmt, std);
3131 }
3132
3133 /* may have to reset 'visit' flag */
3134
3135 nd = get_tbl();
3136 list = clist();
3137 for (i = 0; i < fl.avl; i++) {
3138 plist(list, fl.base[i]);
3139 }
3140 tbl.base[nd].f1 = sptr;
3141 tbl.base[nd].f3 = list;
3142 FREE(fl.base);
3143
3144exit_:
3145 std = STD_NEXT(std);
3146 if (STD_IGNORE(STD_PREV(std)))
3147 delete_stmt(STD_PREV(std));
3148 return std;
3149}
3150
3151static int
3152lhs_dim(int forall, int astli)
3153{
3154 int lhs, lhsd;
3155 int ndim, asd;
3156 int nd;
3157 CTYPE *ct;
3158 int i;
3159
3160 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
3161 ct = FT_CYCLIC(nd);
3162 lhs = ct->lhs;
3163 lhsd = left_subscript_ast(lhs);
3164 asd = A_ASDG(lhsd);
3165 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3166 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
3167 if (ct->idx[i])
3168 if (ASTLI_SPTR(ct->idx[i]) == ASTLI_SPTR(astli))
3169 return i;
3170 }
3171 return -1;
3172}
3173
3174static void
3175conv_fused_forall(int std, int ast, int *stdnextp)
3176{
3177 int i;
3178 int forall;
3179 int nd;
3180 int stmt;
3181 int expr;
3182 int fusedstd;
3183 int exprp, exprn;
3184 int forallp, foralln;
3185 int stdnext = *stdnextp;
3186
3187 nd = A_OPT1G(ast);
3188 if (FT_NFUSE(nd, 0) == 0)
3189 return;
3190
3191 for (i = 0; i < FT_NFUSE(nd, 0); i++) {
3192 fusedstd = FT_FUSEDSTD(nd, 0, i);
3193 forall = STD_AST(fusedstd);
3194 if (i == 0)
3195 exprp = 0;
3196 else {
3197 forallp = STD_AST(FT_FUSEDSTD(nd, 0, i - 1));
3198 exprp = A_IFEXPRG(forallp);
3199 }
3200
3201 if (i == FT_NFUSE(nd, 0) - 1)
3202 exprn = 0;
3203 else {
3204 foralln = STD_AST(FT_FUSEDSTD(nd, 0, i + 1));
3205 exprn = A_IFEXPRG(foralln);
3206 }
3207
3208 if (A_TYPEG(forall) != A_FORALL)
3209 continue;
3210 expr = A_IFEXPRG(forall);
3211 if (expr && !is_same_mask(expr, exprp)) {
3212 insert_mask(expr, STD_PREV(stdnext));
3213 }
3214
3215 stmt = A_IFSTMTG(forall);
3216 if (stmt)
3217 rewrite_asn(stmt, 0, FALSE, MAXSUBS);
3218 if (stmt) {
3219 if (A_SRCG(stmt) != A_DESTG(stmt)) {
3220 add_stmt_before(stmt, stdnext);
3221 }
3222 if (expr && !is_same_mask(expr, exprn))
3223 insert_endmask(expr, STD_PREV(stdnext));
3224 }
3225
3226 if (fusedstd == stdnext) {
3227 *stdnextp = STD_NEXT(stdnext);
3228 }
3229 if (STD_LINENO(std) && STD_LINENO(fusedstd))
3230 ccff_info(MSGFUSE, "FUS030", gbl.findex, STD_LINENO(std),
3231 "Array assignment / Forall at line %linelist fused",
3232 "linelist=%d", STD_LINENO(fusedstd), NULL);
3233 delete_stmt(fusedstd);
3234 }
3235}
3236
3237static LOGICAL
3238is_same_mask(int expr, int expr1)
3239{
3240
3241 LOGICAL l, r;
3242 int argt, argt1;
3243 int sptr, sptr1;
3244 int dim, dim1;
3245 int ast, ast1;
3246 int ndim, ndim1;
3247 int asd, asd1;
3248
3249 if (expr == 0 || expr1 == 0)
3250 return FALSE;
3251 if (A_TYPEG(expr) != A_TYPEG(expr1))
3252 return FALSE;
3253 switch (A_TYPEG(expr)) {
3254 case A_CMPLXC:
3255 case A_CNST:
3256 case A_ID:
3257 case A_SUBSTR:
3258 case A_MEM:
3259 case A_TRIPLE:
3260 case A_LABEL:
3261 if (expr == expr1)
3262 return TRUE;
3263 else
3264 return FALSE;
3265 case A_SUBSCR:
3266 if (expr == expr1)
3267 return TRUE;
3268
3269 sptr = sym_of_ast(expr);
3270 sptr1 = sym_of_ast(expr1);
3271 /* compare a$arrdsc(41) with b$arrdsc(41)
3272 * if a and b distributed the same way this should be equal */
3273 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ARRDSC && STYPEG(sptr1) == ST_ARRDSC) {
3274 asd = A_ASDG(expr);
3275 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3276 asd1 = A_ASDG(expr1);
3277 ndim1 = ASD_NDIM(asd1);
3278 assert(ndim == 1 && ndim == ndim1, "is_same_mask: unmatched ndim", expr,
3279 3);
3280 if (ndim != ndim1)
3281 return FALSE;
3282 if (ASD_SUBS(asd, 0) != ASD_SUBS(asd1, 0))
3283 return FALSE;
3284 sptr = ARRAYG(sptr);
3285 sptr1 = ARRAYG(sptr1);
3286 assert(sptr && sptr1, "is_same_mask: can not find original array", sptr,
3287 3);
3288 if (is_same_array_alignment(sptr, sptr1))
3289 return TRUE;
3290 }
3291 return FALSE;
3292
3293 case A_BINOP:
3294 if (A_DTYPEG(expr) != A_DTYPEG(expr1))
3295 return FALSE;
3296 if (A_OPTYPEG(expr) != A_OPTYPEG(expr1))
3297 return FALSE;
3298 l = is_same_mask(A_LOPG(expr), A_LOPG(expr1));
3299 r = is_same_mask(A_ROPG(expr), A_ROPG(expr1));
3300 return l && r;
3301 case A_UNOP:
3302 if (A_DTYPEG(expr) != A_DTYPEG(expr1))
3303 return FALSE;
3304 if (A_OPTYPEG(expr) != A_OPTYPEG(expr1))
3305 return FALSE;
3306 return is_same_mask(A_LOPG(expr), A_LOPG(expr1));
3307 case A_PAREN:
3308 return is_same_mask(A_LOPG(expr), A_LOPG(expr1));
3309 case A_CONV:
3310 if (A_DTYPEG(expr) != A_DTYPEG(expr1))
3311 return FALSE;
3312 return is_same_mask(A_LOPG(expr), A_LOPG(expr1));
3313 case A_INTR:
3314 case A_FUNC:
3315 if (expr == expr1)
3316 return TRUE;
3317 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(expr));
3318 sptr1 = A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(expr1));
3319 if (sptr != sptr1)
3320 return FALSE;
3321 if (strcmp(SYMNAME(sptr), mkRteRtnNm(RTE_islocal_idx)) != 0)
3322 return FALSE;
3323 argt = A_ARGSG(expr);
3324 argt1 = A_ARGSG(expr1);
3325
3326 sptr = ARRAYG(memsym_of_ast(ARGT_ARG(argt, 0)));
3327 dim = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(ARGT_ARG(argt, 1)));
3328 ast = ARGT_ARG(argt, 2);
3329
3330 sptr1 = ARRAYG(memsym_of_ast(ARGT_ARG(argt1, 0)));
3331 dim1 = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(ARGT_ARG(argt1, 1)));
3332 ast1 = ARGT_ARG(argt1, 2);
3333
3334 if (ast != ast1)
3335 return FALSE;
3336
3337 return TRUE;
3338 default:
3339 interr("is_same_mask: unexpected ast", expr, 2);
3340 return FALSE;
3341 }
3342}
3343
3344static LOGICAL
3345is_same_mask_in_fused(int std, int *pos)
3346{
3347 int forall, forall1;
3348 int fusedstd;
3349 int nd;
3350 int expr, expr1;
3351 int i;
3352 CTYPE *ct;
3353 int max;
3354 int ast, src;
3355
3356 /* put all the mask first */
3357 forall = STD_AST(std);
3358 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
3359 ct = FT_CYCLIC(nd);
3360
3361 expr = A_IFEXPRG(forall);
3362 for (i = 0; i < FT_NFUSE(nd, 0); i++) {
3363 fusedstd = FT_FUSEDSTD(nd, 0, i);
3364 forall1 = STD_AST(fusedstd);
3365 expr1 = A_IFEXPRG(forall1);
3366 if (!is_same_mask(expr, expr1))
3367 return FALSE;
3368 }
3369
3370 /* don't let cyclic and block-cyclic to be mask fused */
3371 /* for (i=0;i<7;i++)
3372 if (ct->cb_block[i] || ct->c_init[i]) return FALSE;
3373 */
3374
3375 *pos = position_finder(forall, expr);
3376
3377 /* Find the position of GETs calls at forall */
3378 for (i = 0; i < FT_NMGET(nd); i++) {
3379 ast = glist(FT_MGET(nd), i);
3380 assert(A_TYPEG(ast) == A_HGETSCLR, "find_mask_calls_pos: wrong ast type",
3381 ast, 3);
3382 src = A_SRCG(ast);
3383 max = position_finder(forall, src);
3384 if (max > *pos)
3385 *pos = max;
3386 }
3387
3388 max = find_max_of_mask_calls_pos(forall);
3389 if (max > *pos)
3390 *pos = max;
3391
3392 for (i = 0; i < FT_NFUSE(nd, 0); i++) {
3393 fusedstd = FT_FUSEDSTD(nd, 0, i);
3394 forall1 = STD_AST(fusedstd);
3395 A_IFEXPRP(forall1, 0);
3396 }
3397
3398 return TRUE;
3399}
3400
3401#ifdef FLANG_OUTCONV_UNUSED
3402/* Register the barrier at stdBar for all FORALL statements fused with
3403 * astForall. If bBefore = TRUE, the barrier occurs before the loop. */
3404static void
3405record_fused_barriers(LOGICAL bBefore, int astForall, int stdBar)
3406{
3407 int ift;
3408 int nFused, iFused;
3409 int stdFused;
3410 int astFused;
3411
3412 ift = A_OPT1G(astForall);
3413 if (!ift)
3414 return;
3415 nFused = FT_NFUSE(ift, 0);
3416
3417 for (iFused = 0; iFused < nFused; iFused++) {
3418 stdFused = FT_FUSEDSTD(ift, 0, iFused);
3419 astFused = STD_AST(stdFused);
3420 if (!astFused)
3421 continue;
3422 record_barrier(bBefore, astFused, stdBar);
3423 }
3424}
3425#endif
3426
3427int
3428conv_forall(int std)
3429{
3430 int forall;
3431 int stmt;
3432 int newast;
3433 int stdnext;
3434 int triplet_list;
3435 int triplet;
3436 int index_var;
3437 int n;
3438 int expr;
3439 int std1;
3440 int ldim;
3441 int nd;
3442 CTYPE *ct;
3443 int i;
3444 int revers[7];
3445 int pos, cnt;
3446 LOGICAL samemask;
3447 int lhs_sptr, lhs_ast;
3448 int doifstmt, ifexpr, zero;
3449 int stride, tmp_ifexpr;
3450
3451 stdnext = STD_NEXT(std);
3452 if (no_effect_forall(std))
3453 return stdnext;
3454
3455 forall = STD_AST(std);
3456 n = 0;
3457 triplet_list = A_LISTG(forall);
3458 for (; triplet_list; triplet_list = ASTLI_NEXT(triplet_list))
3459 n++;
3460 find_mask_calls_pos(forall);
3461 pos = n;
3462 samemask = is_same_mask_in_fused(std, &pos);
3463 find_stmt_calls_pos(forall, pos);
3464
3465 n = 0;
3466 triplet_list = A_LISTG(forall);
3467 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
3468 lhs_ast = left_subscript_ast(A_DESTG(A_IFSTMTG(forall)));
3469 lhs_sptr = memsym_of_ast(lhs_ast);
3470
3471 ct = FT_CYCLIC(nd);
3472 if (ct->ifast)
3473 insert_mask(A_IFEXPRG(ct->ifast), STD_PREV(stdnext));
3474
3475 doifstmt = 1; /* only place if stmt if stride is 1 for now */
3476 ifexpr = 0;
3477 for (; triplet_list; triplet_list = ASTLI_NEXT(triplet_list)) {
3478 revers[n] = triplet_list;
3479 n++;
3480 ldim = 0;
3481 triplet = ASTLI_TRIPLE(triplet_list);
3482
3483 if (!XBIT(34, 0x8000000)) {
3484 if (DTY(DT_INT) != TY_INT8 && !XBIT(68, 0x1)) {
3485 zero = astb.i0;
3486 } else {
3487 zero = astb.bnd.zero;
3488 }
3489 tmp_ifexpr = mk_binop(OP_SUB, A_UPBDG(triplet), A_LBDG(triplet),
3490 A_DTYPEG(A_LBDG(triplet)));
3491 if (A_STRIDEG(triplet) != astb.i1) {
3492 stride = A_STRIDEG(triplet);
3493 if (stride == 0)
3494 stride = astb.i1;
3495 } else {
3496 stride = astb.i1;
3497 }
3498 tmp_ifexpr =
3499 mk_binop(OP_ADD, tmp_ifexpr, stride, A_DTYPEG(A_LBDG(triplet)));
3500 tmp_ifexpr =
3501 mk_binop(OP_DIV, tmp_ifexpr, stride, A_DTYPEG(A_LBDG(triplet)));
3502 tmp_ifexpr = mk_binop(OP_LE, tmp_ifexpr, zero, DT_LOG);
3503 if (ifexpr) {
3504 ifexpr = mk_binop(OP_LOR, tmp_ifexpr, ifexpr, DT_LOG);
3505 } else {
3506 ifexpr = tmp_ifexpr;
3507 }
3508 }
3509
3510 if (ct->lhs)
3511 ldim = lhs_dim(forall, triplet_list);
3512 if (ldim >= 0) {
3513 if (ct->cb_init[ldim])
3514 add_stmt_before(ct->cb_init[ldim], stdnext);
3515 if (ct->cb_do[ldim])
3516 add_stmt_before(ct->cb_do[ldim], stdnext);
3517 if (ct->cb_block[ldim]) {
3518 int astBlock = ct->cb_block[ldim];
3519 int astCall, ast1;
3520 int argt;
3521 int dim;
3522
3523 if (normalize_bounds(lhs_sptr)) {
3524 assert(A_TYPEG(astBlock) == A_CALL && A_ARGCNTG(astBlock) == 8,
3525 "conv_forall: missing block_loop", std, 4);
3526 argt = A_ARGSG(astBlock);
3527 dim = get_int_cval(A_SPTRG(ARGT_ARG(argt, 1))) - 1;
3528 assert(ldim == dim, "conv_forall: missing dim in block_loop", std, 4);
3529
3530 astCall = begin_call(A_CALL, sym_of_ast(A_LOPG(astBlock)), 8);
3531 add_arg(ARGT_ARG(argt, 0)); /* descriptor */
3532 add_arg(ARGT_ARG(argt, 1)); /* dimension */
3533
3534 /* Normalize the lower bound. */
3535 ast1 = ARGT_ARG(argt, 2);
3536 ast1 = sub_lbnd(DTYPEG(lhs_sptr), dim, ast1, lhs_ast);
3537 add_arg(ast1); /* lower bound */
3538
3539 /* Normalize the upper bound. */
3540 ast1 = ARGT_ARG(argt, 3);
3541 ast1 = sub_lbnd(DTYPEG(lhs_sptr), dim, ast1, lhs_ast);
3542 add_arg(ast1); /* upper bound */
3543
3544 add_arg(ARGT_ARG(argt, 4)); /* stride */
3545
3546 add_arg(ARGT_ARG(argt, 5)); /* cycle # */
3547
3548 add_arg(ARGT_ARG(argt, 6)); /* output lower bound */
3549 add_arg(ARGT_ARG(argt, 7)); /* output upper bound */
3550 add_stmt_before(astCall, stdnext);
3551
3552 ast1 = add_lbnd(DTYPEG(lhs_sptr), dim, ARGT_ARG(argt, 6), lhs_ast);
3553 ast1 = mk_assn_stmt(ARGT_ARG(argt, 6), ast1, DT_INT);
3554 add_stmt_before(ast1, stdnext);
3555
3556 ast1 = add_lbnd(DTYPEG(lhs_sptr), dim, ARGT_ARG(argt, 7), lhs_ast);
3557 ast1 = mk_assn_stmt(ARGT_ARG(argt, 7), ast1, DT_INT);
3558 add_stmt_before(ast1, stdnext);
3559 } else
3560 add_stmt_before(astBlock, stdnext);
3561 }
3562 }
3563 }
3564 /* don't do one dimension */
3565 if (n <= 1 || STD_ZTRIP(std) != 1)
3566 doifstmt = 0;
3567
3568 triplet_list = A_LISTG(forall);
3569
3570 cnt = 0;
3571 for (; triplet_list; triplet_list = ASTLI_NEXT(triplet_list)) {
3572 int dovar, tstd;
3573 ldim = 0;
3574 if (ct->lhs)
3575 ldim = lhs_dim(forall, triplet_list);
3576 if (ldim >= 0 && ct->c_init[ldim])
3577 add_stmt_before(ct->c_init[ldim], stdnext);
3578
3579 add_mask_calls(cnt, forall, stdnext);
3580
3581 if (samemask && cnt == pos) {
3582 expr = A_IFEXPRG(forall);
3583 if (expr)
3584 insert_mask(expr, STD_PREV(stdnext));
3585 }
3586
3587 add_stmt_calls(cnt, forall, stdnext);
3588
3589 index_var = ASTLI_SPTR(triplet_list);
3590 triplet = ASTLI_TRIPLE(triplet_list);
3591
3592 newast = mk_stmt(A_DO, 0);
3593 dovar = mk_id(index_var);
3594 A_DOVARP(newast, dovar);
3595 A_M1P(newast, A_LBDG(triplet));
3596 A_M2P(newast, A_UPBDG(triplet));
3597 if (A_STRIDEG(triplet) != astb.i1) {
3598 A_M3P(newast, A_STRIDEG(triplet));
3599 } else {
3600 A_M3P(newast, astb.i1);
3601 }
3602 A_M4P(newast, ifexpr);
3603
3604 tstd = add_stmt_before(newast, stdnext);
3605
3606 STD_ZTRIP(tstd) = 0;
3607 if (doifstmt && !XBIT(34, 0x8000000)) {
3608 STD_ZTRIP(tstd) = 1;
3609 }
3610
3611 cnt++;
3612 }
3613
3614 add_mask_calls(cnt, forall, stdnext);
3615
3616 if (cnt == pos) {
3617 expr = A_IFEXPRG(forall);
3618 if (expr)
3619 insert_mask(expr, STD_PREV(stdnext));
3620 }
3621
3622 add_stmt_calls(cnt, forall, stdnext);
3623
3624 if (ct->inner_cyclic)
3625 for (i = 0; i < ct->inner_cyclic->nitem; i++)
3626 add_stmt_before(glist(ct->inner_cyclic, i), stdnext);
3627
3628 stmt = A_IFSTMTG(forall);
3629
3630 /*
3631 plist = FT_PCALL(nd);
3632 for(ip = 0; ip< FT_NPCALL(nd); ip++) {
3633 pstd = plist->item;
3634 plist = plist->next;
3635 past = STD_AST(pstd);
3636 delete_stmt(pstd);
3637 pstd=add_stmt_before(past, stdnext);
3638 pghpf_local_mode = 1;
3639 transform_ast(pstd, past);
3640 pghpf_local_mode = 0;
3641 }
3642 */
3643 arg_gbl.std = stdnext;
3644 rewrite_asn(stmt, 0, FALSE, MAXSUBS);
3645 if (stmt) {
3646 /* perhaps should move this part related to elemental function
3647 * to another function.
3648 * At this point, a function is already converted to a subroutine call.
3649 * It was done in semfunc.c in func_call().
3650 */
3651 int ast;
3652 int rhs = A_SRCG(stmt);
3653 int lhs = A_DESTG(stmt);
3654 int func_ast = 0;
3655 int func_sptr = 0;
3656 int dt = 0;
3657 int afunc = 0;
3658
3659 if ((afunc = (A_TYPEG(rhs) == A_FUNC))) {
3660 func_ast = A_LOPG(rhs);
3661 func_sptr = A_SPTRG(func_ast);
3662 dt = DTYPEG(func_sptr);
3663 }
3664 if (afunc && func_sptr && ELEMENTALG(func_sptr) && ADJLENG(func_sptr)) {
3665 int argcnt, argt;
3666 int result_sptr = A_SPTRG(ARGT_ARG(A_ARGSG(rhs), 0));
3667 int result_ast = mk_id(result_sptr);
3668
3669 /* make A_CALL instead of A_FUNC */
3670 argcnt = A_ARGCNTG(rhs);
3671 argt = mk_argt(argcnt);
3672 ast = mk_func_node(A_CALL, mk_id(func_sptr), argcnt, A_ARGSG(rhs));
3673 std = add_stmt_before(ast, stdnext);
3674
3675 /* b(i) = scalar_temp */
3676 ast = mk_assn_stmt(lhs, result_ast, dt);
3677 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
3678 rewrite_asn(ast, 0, FALSE, MAXSUBS);
3679 } else if (A_TYPEG(rhs) == A_INTR &&
3680 (A_OPTYPEG(rhs) == I_ADJUSTL || A_OPTYPEG(rhs) == I_ADJUSTR)) {
3681 /* make a scalar temp instead of an array to avoid allocating memory. In
3682 the case of adjust(l/r) the size of result string is same as incoming
3683 string. So, storing the return value can be optimized out. Hence, the
3684 use of a scalar temp.
3685 */
3686 lhs = mk_id(get_temp(DT_INT));
3687 ast = mk_assn_stmt(lhs, rhs, dt);
3688 add_stmt_before(ast, stdnext);
3689 } else if (A_TYPEG(rhs) == A_INTR && A_OPTYPEG(rhs) == I_TRIM) {
3690 /* In case of trim, the return value needs to be retained as the size
3691 of the returning string may change, hence the incoming lhs with an
3692 array of temps need to be retained.
3693 */
3694 ast = mk_assn_stmt(lhs, rhs, dt);
3695 add_stmt_before(ast, stdnext);
3696 } else if (A_SRCG(stmt) != A_DESTG(stmt)) {
3697 add_stmt_before(stmt, stdnext);
3698 }
3699 if (!samemask && expr)
3700 insert_endmask(expr, STD_PREV(stdnext));
3701
3702 conv_fused_forall(std, forall, &stdnext);
3703
3704 for (i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
3705 int tstd;
3706 triplet_list = revers[i];
3707 if (samemask && i + 1 == pos && expr)
3708 insert_endmask(expr, STD_PREV(stdnext));
3709
3710 ldim = 0;
3711 if (ct->lhs)
3712 ldim = lhs_dim(forall, triplet_list);
3713 if (ldim >= 0 && ct->c_inc[ldim])
3714 add_stmt_before(ct->c_inc[ldim], stdnext);
3715
3716 newast = mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0);
3717 tstd = add_stmt_before(newast, stdnext);
3718 if (doifstmt)
3719 STD_ZTRIP(tstd) = 1;
3720 }
3721
3722 if (samemask && i + 1 == pos && expr)
3723 insert_endmask(expr, STD_PREV(stdnext));
3724 for (i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
3725 triplet_list = revers[i];
3726 ldim = 0;
3727 if (ct->lhs)
3728 ldim = lhs_dim(forall, triplet_list);
3729 if (ldim >= 0) {
3730 if (ct->cb_inc[ldim])
3731 add_stmt_before(ct->cb_inc[ldim], stdnext);
3732 if (ct->cb_enddo[ldim])
3733 add_stmt_before(ct->cb_enddo[ldim], stdnext);
3734 }
3735 }
3736 if (ct->endifast)
3737 insert_endmask(A_IFEXPRG(ct->ifast), STD_PREV(stdnext));
3738 } else {
3739 int tstd;
3740 while (TRUE) {
3741 std1 = stdnext;
3742 stmt = STD_AST(stdnext);
3743 stdnext = STD_NEXT(stdnext);
3744 if (A_TYPEG(stmt) == A_ENDFORALL) {
3745 if (expr)
3746 insert_endmask(expr, STD_PREV(stdnext));
3747 newast = mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0);
3748 while (n--) {
3749 tstd = add_stmt_before(newast, stdnext);
3750 if (doifstmt)
3751 STD_ZTRIP(tstd) = 1;
3752 }
3753 delete_stmt(std); /* delete forall */
3754 delete_stmt(std1); /* delede endforall */
3755 break;
3756 } else if (A_TYPEG(stmt) == A_FORALL)
3757 stdnext = conv_forall(std);
3758 assert(stdnext, "conv_forall:unmatched forall", std, 4);
3759 }
3760 }
3761
3762 /* fix up line numbers and propagate par flag */
3763 for (i = std; i != stdnext; i = STD_NEXT(i)) {
3764 STD_LINENO(i) = STD_LINENO(std);
3765 STD_PAR(i) = STD_PAR(std);
3766 STD_TASK(i) = STD_TASK(std);
3767 STD_ACCEL(i) = STD_ACCEL(std);
3768 STD_KERNEL(i) = STD_KERNEL(std);
3769 }
3770
3771 /* for parallel PURE calls */
3772 pure_gbl.local_mode = 1;
3773 search_pure_function(std, stdnext);
3774 pure_gbl.local_mode = 0;
3775 ast_to_comment(forall);
3776 return stdnext;
3777}
3778
3779static void
3780replace_loop_on_fuse_list(int oldloop, int maskloop)
3781{
3782 int nd = A_OPT1G(STD_AST(oldloop));
3783 int head = FT_HEADER(nd);
3784 int nfused;
3785 int i;
3786 nd = A_OPT1G(STD_AST(head));
3787 nfused = FT_NFUSE(nd, 0);
3788 for (i = 0; i < nfused; i++) {
3789 if (FT_FUSEDSTD(nd, 0, i) == oldloop) {
3790 FT_FUSEDSTD(nd, 0, i) = maskloop;
3791 break;
3792 }
3793 }
3794}
3795
3796/* ast for forall */
3797/* ast for subscript expression */
3798/* statement before which to allocate temp */
3799/* statement after which to deallocate temp */
3800/* datatype, or zero */
3801/* ast with data type of element required */
3802static int
3803get_temp_forall2(int forall_ast, int subscr_ast, int alloc_stmt,
3804 int dealloc_stmt, int dty, int ast_dty)
3805{
3806 int sptr = 0, astd, dstd, asd = 0;
3807 int subscr[MAXSUBS];
3808 int par, ndim, lp, std, fg, fg2, lp2;
3809 int save_sc;
3810 int dtype = dty ? dty : (DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast_dty)));
3811 int cvlen = 0;
3812 T_LIST *q;
3813 lp = 0;
3814 cvlen = 0;
3815 std = alloc_stmt;
3816
3817 fg = STD_FG(std);
3818 if (A_TYPEG(subscr_ast) == A_MEM) {
3819 goto new_sptr;
3820 /* subscr_ast = A_PARENTG(subscr_ast); */
3821 }
3822 asd = A_ASDG(subscr_ast);
3823 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3824
3825 if (fg)
3826 lp = FG_LOOP(fg);
3827 else
3828 goto new_sptr;
3829
3830 if (!lp)
3831 goto new_sptr;
3832
3833 if (LP_MEXITS(lp))
3834 goto new_sptr;
3835
3836 /* don't do char for now */
3837 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR)
3838 goto new_sptr;
3839
3840 add_loop_hd(lp);
3841
3842 /* notes that loop may change when we re-init */
3843 for (q = templist; q; q = q->next) {
3844 fg2 = STD_FG(q->std);
3845 if (fg2)
3846 lp2 = FG_LOOP(fg2);
3847 else
3848 continue;
3849 if (!lp2)
3850 continue;
3851
3852 if (q->std == std || q->dtype != dtype || q->cvlen != cvlen ||
3853 q->sc != symutl.sc || LP_PARENT(lp2) != LP_PARENT(lp))
3854 continue;
3855
3856 if (ndim != ASD_NDIM(q->asd))
3857 continue;
3858 if (same_forall_size(lp2, lp, 0)) {
3859#if DEBUG
3860 if (DBGBIT(43, 0x800)) {
3861 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "Reuse tmp array ostd:%d new:%d sptr:%d\n", q->std,
3862 std, sptr);
3863 }
3864#endif
3865
3866 /* add and remove stmts to flowgraph */
3867 rdilts(fg);
3868 dstd = mk_mem_deallocate(mk_id(q->temp), dealloc_stmt);
3869 FG_STDLAST(fg) = dstd;
3870 wrilts(fg);
3871
3872 rdilts(fg2);
3873 FG_STDLAST(fg2) = STD_PREV(FG_STDLAST(fg2));
3874 wrilts(fg2);
3875
3876 ast_to_comment(STD_AST(q->dstd));
3877 q->dstd = dstd;
3878 q->std = std;
3879 STD_HSTBLE(q->astd) = dstd;
3880 STD_HSTBLE(q->dstd) = q->astd;
3881 par = STD_PAR(alloc_stmt) || STD_TASK(alloc_stmt);
3882 if (par) {
3883 save_sc = symutl.sc;
3884 set_descriptor_sc(SC_PRIVATE);
3885 }
3886 if (dty) {
3887 sptr = get_forall_subscr(forall_ast, subscr_ast, subscr, dty);
3888 } else {
3889 sptr = get_forall_subscr(forall_ast, subscr_ast, subscr,
3890 DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast_dty)));
3891 }
3892 if (par) {
3893 set_descriptor_sc(save_sc);
3894 }
3895 return q->temp;
3896 }
3897 }
3898new_sptr:
3899 par = STD_PAR(alloc_stmt) || STD_TASK(alloc_stmt);
3900 if (par) {
3901 save_sc = symutl.sc;
3902 set_descriptor_sc(SC_PRIVATE);
3903 }
3904
3905 if (dty) {
3906 sptr = mk_forall_sptr(forall_ast, subscr_ast, subscr, dty);
3907 } else {
3908 sptr =
3909 mk_forall_sptr(forall_ast, subscr_ast, subscr, DDTG(A_DTYPEG(ast_dty)));
3910 }
3911 if (par) {
3912 set_descriptor_sc(save_sc);
3913 }
3914
3915 if (fg) {
3916 rdilts(fg);
3917 }
3918 astd = mk_mem_allocate(mk_id(sptr), subscr, alloc_stmt, ast_dty);
3919 dstd = mk_mem_deallocate(mk_id(sptr), dealloc_stmt);
3920 if (fg)
3921 wrilts(fg);
3922
3923 if (!par) {
3924 STD_HSTBLE(astd) = dstd;
3925 STD_HSTBLE(dstd) = astd;
3926 if (STD_ACCEL(alloc_stmt))
3927 STD_RESCOPE(astd) = 1;
3928 if (STD_ACCEL(dealloc_stmt))
3929 STD_RESCOPE(dstd) = 1;
3930 }
3931
3932 GET_T_LIST(q);
3933 q->next = templist;
3934 templist = q;
3935 q->temp = sptr;
3936 q->asd = asd;
3937 q->dtype = dtype;
3938 q->cvlen = cvlen;
3939 q->std = std;
3940 q->sc = symutl.sc;
3941 q->astd = astd;
3942 q->dstd = dstd;
3943
3944 return sptr;
3945}
3946
3947static LOGICAL
3948is_pointer(int ast)
3949{
3950 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR)
3951 ast = A_LOPG(ast);
3952 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_MEM)
3953 ast = A_MEMG(ast);
3954 if (A_TYPEG(ast) != A_ID)
3955 return FALSE;
3956 if (POINTERG(A_SPTRG(ast)))
3957 return TRUE;
3958 return FALSE;
3959}
3960
3961/* This routine is to check whether forall has dependency.
3962 * If it has, it creates temp which is shape array with lhs.
3963 * For example,
3964 * forall(i=1:N) a(i) = a(i-1)+.....
3965 * will be rewritten
3966 * forall(i=1:N) temp(i) = a(i-1)+.....
3967 * forall(i=1:N) a(i) = temp(i)
3968 */
3969
3970/*
3971 * This routine assumes that input is block forall with an assignment
3972 * statement in it.
3973 */
3974static void
3975forall_dependency(int std)
3976{
3977 int lhs, rhs;
3978 int asn;
3979 int sptr;
3980 int temp_ast;
3981 int newasn;
3982 int forall;
3983 int newforall;
3984 int newstd;
3985 int nd;
3986 int header;
3987 int lineno;
3988 LOGICAL bIndep, isdepend;
3989 int sptr_lhs;
3990 CTYPE *ct;
3991 int lhso;
3992 int par;
3993 int task;
3994 int expr;
3995
3996 forall = STD_AST(std);
3997 par = STD_PAR(std);
3998 task = STD_TASK(std);
3999 asn = A_IFSTMTG(forall);
4000 lhs = A_DESTG(asn);
4001 sptr_lhs = sym_of_ast(lhs);
4002 rhs = A_SRCG(asn);
4003 expr = A_IFEXPRG(forall);
4004
4005 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4006 header = FT_HEADER(nd);
4007 /* find pointer original lhs */
4008 if (POINTERG(sptr_lhs)) {
4009 ct = FT_CYCLIC(nd);
4010 if (ct && ct->lhs)
4011 lhso = ct->lhs;
4012 else
4013 lhso = lhs;
4014 } else
4015 lhso = lhs;
4016
4017 /* forall-independent */
4018 lineno = STD_LINENO(std);
4019 open_pragma(lineno);
4020 bIndep = XBIT(19, 0x100) != 0;
4021 if (bIndep) {
4022 close_pragma();
4023 return;
4024 }
4025
4026 /* take conditional expr, if there is dependency */
4027 if (expr)
4028 if (is_dependent(lhs, expr, forall, std, std) ||
4029 is_mask_call_dependent(forall, lhs)) {
4030 if (flg.opt >= 2 && !XBIT(2, 0x400000)) {
4031 if (is_pointer(lhs) && !lhs_needtmp(lhs, rhs, std))
4032 return;
4033 /* get_temp_forall2() is defined in this file */
4034 sptr = get_temp_forall2(forall, lhs, header, std, DT_LOG, 0);
4035 } else {
4036 /* symutl.c:get_temp_forall() */
4037 sptr = get_temp_forall(forall, lhs, header, std, DT_LOG, 0);
4038 }
4039 if (flg.opt >= 2 && !XBIT(2, 0x400000))
4040 temp_ast = reference_for_temp(sptr, lhs, forall);
4041 else
4042 temp_ast = reference_for_temp(sptr, lhso, forall);
4043 A_IFEXPRP(forall, temp_ast);
4044 newforall = mk_stmt(A_FORALL, 0);
4045 A_LISTP(newforall, A_LISTG(forall));
4046 A_OPT1P(newforall, A_OPT1G(forall));
4047 A_IFEXPRP(newforall, 0);
4048 newasn = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
4049 A_DESTP(newasn, temp_ast);
4050 A_SRCP(newasn, expr);
4051 A_IFSTMTP(newforall, newasn);
4052 move_mask_calls(newforall);
4053 remove_mask_calls(newforall);
4054 remove_mask_calls(forall);
4055 newstd = add_stmt_before(newforall, std);
4056 STD_PAR(newstd) = par;
4057 STD_TASK(newstd) = task;
4058
4059 /* add the newstd to the std fuse list */
4060 replace_loop_on_fuse_list(std, newstd);
4061
4062 report_comm(std, DEPENDENCY_CAUSE);
4063 un_fuse(forall);
4064 un_fuse(newforall);
4065
4066 /* need to add this to flow graph otherwise add_loop_hd will drop it */
4067 if (flg.opt >= 2 && !XBIT(2, 0x400000)) {
4068 int fg = STD_FG(std);
4069 int newfg = add_fg(FG_LPREV(fg));
4070 FG_STDLAST(newfg) = newstd;
4071 FG_STDFIRST(newfg) = newstd;
4072 }
4073 }
4074
4075 isdepend = is_dependent(lhs, rhs, forall, std, std);
4076 if (isdepend || is_stmt_call_dependent(forall, lhs)) {
4077 if (flg.opt >= 2 && !XBIT(2, 0x400000)) {
4078 if (is_pointer(lhs) && !lhs_needtmp(lhs, rhs, std)) {
4079 return;
4080 }
4081 /* get_temp_forall2() is defined in this file */
4082 sptr = get_temp_forall2(forall, lhs, header, std, 0, lhs);
4083 } else {
4084 /* symutl.c:get_temp_forall() */
4085 sptr = get_temp_forall(forall, lhs, header, std, 0, lhs);
4086 }
4087 if (flg.opt >= 2 && !XBIT(2, 0x400000))
4088 temp_ast = reference_for_temp(sptr, lhs, forall);
4089 else
4090 temp_ast = reference_for_temp(sptr, lhso, forall);
4091 A_DESTP(asn, temp_ast);
4092 A_IFSTMTP(forall, asn);
4093 newforall = mk_stmt(A_FORALL, 0);
4094 A_LISTP(newforall, A_LISTG(forall));
4095 A_OPT1P(newforall, A_OPT1G(forall));
4096 A_IFEXPRP(newforall, A_IFEXPRG(forall));
4097 newasn = mk_stmt(A_ASN, 0);
4098 A_DESTP(newasn, lhs);
4099 A_SRCP(newasn, temp_ast);
4100 A_IFSTMTP(newforall, newasn);
4101 remove_mask_calls(newforall);
4102 remove_stmt_calls(newforall);
4103 newstd = add_stmt_after(newforall, std);
4104 STD_PAR(newstd) = par;
4105 STD_TASK(newstd) = task;
4106 report_comm(std, DEPENDENCY_CAUSE);
4107 un_fuse(forall);
4108 un_fuse(newforall);
4109 }
4110 close_pragma();
4111}
4112
4113static LOGICAL
4114is_stmt_call_dependent(int forall, int lhs)
4115{
4116 int nd;
4117 int cstd;
4118 int i;
4119 LOGICAL l;
4120
4121 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4122 for (i = 0; i < FT_NSCALL(nd); i++) {
4123 cstd = glist(FT_SCALL(nd), i);
4124 l = is_call_dependent(cstd, forall, lhs);
4125 if (l)
4126 return TRUE;
4127 }
4128 return FALSE;
4129}
4130
4131static LOGICAL
4132is_mask_call_dependent(int forall, int lhs)
4133{
4134 int nd;
4135 int cstd;
4136 int i;
4137 LOGICAL l;
4138
4139 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4140 for (i = 0; i < FT_NMCALL(nd); i++) {
4141 cstd = glist(FT_MCALL(nd), i);
4142 l = is_call_dependent(cstd, forall, lhs);
4143 if (l)
4144 return TRUE;
4145 }
4146 return FALSE;
4147}
4148
4149static LOGICAL
4150is_call_dependent(int std, int forall, int lhs)
4151{
4152 int ast, ast1;
4153 int std1;
4154 int nd, nd1;
4155 int i;
4156 int argt;
4157 int nargs;
4158 LOGICAL l;
4159
4160 ast = STD_AST(std);
4161 nd = A_OPT1G(ast);
4162 assert(nd, "is_call_dependent: uninitialized pure call", ast, 3);
4163 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
4164 argt = A_ARGSG(ast);
4165 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
4166 l = is_dependent(lhs, ARGT_ARG(argt, i), forall, std, std);
4167 if (l)
4168 return TRUE;
4169 }
4170
4171 for (i = 0; i < FT_CALL_NCALL(nd); i++) {
4172 std1 = glist(FT_CALL_CALL(nd), i);
4173 ast1 = STD_AST(std1);
4174 nd1 = A_OPT1G(ast1);
4175 assert(nd1, "is_call_dependent: uninitialized pure call", ast1, 3);
4176 l = is_call_dependent(std1, forall, lhs);
4177 if (l)
4178 return TRUE;
4179 }
4180 return FALSE;
4181}
4182
4183static void
4184move_mask_calls(int forall)
4185{
4186 int nd;
4187 int nd1;
4188
4189 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4190 nd1 = mk_ftb();
4191 BCOPY(ftb.base + nd1, ftb.base + nd, FT, 1);
4192 FT_NSCALL(nd1) = FT_NMCALL(nd);
4193 FT_SCALL(nd1) = FT_MCALL(nd);
4194 FT_NSGET(nd1) = FT_NMGET(nd);
4195 FT_SGET(nd1) = FT_MGET(nd);
4196 A_OPT1P(forall, nd1);
4197}
4198static void
4199remove_mask_calls(int forall)
4200{
4201 int nd;
4202 int nd1;
4203
4204 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4205 nd1 = mk_ftb();
4206 BCOPY(ftb.base + nd1, ftb.base + nd, FT, 1);
4207 FT_NMCALL(nd1) = 0;
4208 FT_MCALL(nd1) = clist();
4209 FT_NMGET(nd1) = 0;
4210 FT_MGET(nd1) = clist();
4211 A_OPT1P(forall, nd1);
4212}
4213
4214static void
4215remove_stmt_calls(int forall)
4216{
4217 int nd;
4218 int nd1;
4219
4220 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4221 nd1 = mk_ftb();
4222 BCOPY(ftb.base + nd1, ftb.base + nd, FT, 1);
4223 FT_NSCALL(nd1) = 0;
4224 FT_SCALL(nd1) = clist();
4225 FT_NSGET(nd1) = 0;
4226 FT_SGET(nd1) = clist();
4227 A_OPT1P(forall, nd1);
4228}
4229
4230/* This routine return TRUE if there is a possiblity that
4231 * sptr is pointer and points sptr1 or
4232 * sptr1 is pointer and points sptr
4233 * otherwise return FALSE;
4234 * ### add pointer target information here
4235 */
4236LOGICAL
4237is_pointer_dependent(int sptr, int sptr1)
4238{
4239 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) != DTY(DTYPEG(sptr1)))
4240 return FALSE;
4241 if (POINTERG(sptr))
4242 if (POINTERG(sptr1) || TARGETG(sptr1))
4243 return TRUE;
4244
4245 if (POINTERG(sptr1))
4246 if (POINTERG(sptr) || TARGETG(sptr))
4247 return TRUE;
4248 return FALSE;
4249}
4250
4251/* ARRAY COLLAPSING */
4252
4253/* typedefs for array collapsing */
4254typedef struct {
4255 int astArr; /* SUBSCR AST of compiler-created array */
4256 int stdAlloc; /* STD of allocate statement for astArr */
4257 int stdDealloc; /* STD of deallocate statement for astArr */
4258 int lp; /* loop # defs of astArr */
4259 int astSclr; /* AST of new scalar */
4260 union {
4261 INT16 all;
4262 struct {
4263 unsigned descr : 1; /* found use of the array's descriptor */
4264 unsigned delete : 1; /* entry has been deleted */
4265 } bits;
4266 } flags;
4267} COLLAPSE;
4268
4269/* macros for array collapsing */
4270#define COLLAPSE_ASTARR(i) collapse.base[i].astArr
4271#define COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(i) collapse.base[i].stdAlloc
4272#define COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(i) collapse.base[i].stdDealloc
4273#define COLLAPSE_LP(i) collapse.base[i].lp
4274#define COLLAPSE_ASTSCLR(i) collapse.base[i].astSclr
4275#define COLLAPSE_DESCR(i) collapse.base[i].flags.bits.descr
4276#define COLLAPSE_DELETE(i) collapse.base[i].flags.bits.delete
4277
4278/* local storage for array collapsing */
4279static struct {
4280 COLLAPSE *base; /* the COLLAPSE table */
4281 int size; /* size of the COLLAPSE table */
4282 int avail; /* next available struct in the COLLAPSE table */
4283 int lp; /* current loop */
4284 int std; /* current STD */
4285} collapse;
4286
4287static void
4288init_collapse(void)
4289{
4290 /* Initialize local storage. */
4291 collapse.size = 100;
4292 NEW(collapse.base, COLLAPSE, collapse.size);
4293 collapse.avail = 1;
4294}
4295
4296/* Replace all compiler-created temp arrays that are used only within
4297 * one loop with scalars. */
4298static void
4299collapse_arrays(void)
4300{
4301 int ast;
4302 int ci;
4303 int sptrArr, sptrSclr;
4304 int nscalars;
4305
4306 /* Scan STDs looking for ALLOCATE/DEALLOCATE statements. */
4307 find_collapse_allocs();
4308
4309 /* Build the loop table. */
4310 hlopt_init(0);
4311#if DEBUG
4312 if (DBGBIT(43, 1))
4313 dump_flowgraph();
4314#endif
4315#if DEBUG
4316 if (DBGBIT(43, 4))
4317 dump_loops();
4318#endif
4319
4320 /* Determine if all defs of each array are within a single loop. */
4321 find_collapse_defs();
4322
4323 /* Determine if all uses of each array are within their defining loops. */
4324 find_collapse_uses();
4325
4326 /* Create new scalars */
4327 nscalars = 0;
4328 for (ci = 1; ci < collapse.avail; ci++) {
4329 if (COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci))
4330 continue;
4331 if (!COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci) || A_TYPEG(COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci)) != A_SUBSCR) {
4332 delete_collapse(ci);
4333 continue;
4334 }
4335 sptrArr = memsym_of_ast(COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci));
4336 sptrSclr = sym_get_scalar(SYMNAME(sptrArr), "s", DDTG(DTYPEG(sptrArr)));
4337 COLLAPSE_ASTSCLR(ci) = mk_id(sptrSclr);
4338 nscalars++;
4339 }
4340
4341 if (nscalars)
4342 /* Collapse all arrays within the current program unit. */
4343 collapse_loops();
4344
4345/* List loops containing collapsed arrays. */
4346#if DEBUG
4347 if (DBGBIT(43, 256))
4348 report_collapse(0);
4349#endif
4350
4351 /* Mark arrays with uses of array descriptors. */
4352 find_descrs();
4353
4354 /* Delete ALLOCATE/DEALLOCATE statements for arrays without uses of
4355 * array descriptors. */
4356 collapse_allocates(FALSE);
4357
4358 /* Reclaim storage. */
4359 for (ast = 1; ast < astb.stg_avail; ast++)
4360 A_OPT2P(ast, 0);
4361 hlopt_end(0, 0);
4362
4363#if DEBUG
4364 if (DBGBIT(43, 128)) {
4365 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "----- Statements after array collapsing -----\n");
4366 dump_std();
4367 }
4368#endif
4369}
4370
4371/* Frees memory used to collapse arrays. */
4372static void
4373end_collapse(void)
4374{
4375 FREE(collapse.base);
4376}
4377
4378/* For each ALLOCATE of a compiler-created array, initialize an entry
4379 * within the COLLAPSE table. Set the OPT2 field of the
4380 * array's AST to the index of its COLLAPSE table entry. */
4381static void
4382find_collapse_allocs(void)
4383{
4384 int std;
4385 int ast, astSrc, astArr;
4386 int ci;
4387
4388 for (std = STD_NEXT(0); std; std = STD_NEXT(std)) {
4389 ast = STD_AST(std);
4390 if (A_TYPEG(ast) != A_ALLOC)
4391 continue;
4392 astSrc = A_SRCG(ast);
4393 if (A_TKNG(ast) == TK_ALLOCATE) {
4394 if (A_TYPEG(astSrc) != A_SUBSCR)
4395 continue; /* ...must be pointer ALLOCATE. */
4396 astArr = A_LOPG(astSrc);
4397 if (A_TYPEG(astArr) != A_ID)
4398 continue;
4399 if (!HCCSYMG(A_SPTRG(astArr)) || !VCSYMG(A_SPTRG(astArr)))
4400 continue; /* array not compiler created */
4401 ci = A_OPT2G(astArr);
4402 if (ci) {
4403 delete_collapse(ci); /* multiple ALLOCATEs found */
4404 continue;
4405 }
4406
4407 /* Create a new COLLAPSE structure. */
4408 ci = collapse.avail++;
4409 NEED(collapse.avail, collapse.base, COLLAPSE, collapse.size,
4410 collapse.size + 100);
4411 BZERO(&collapse.base[ci], COLLAPSE, 1);
4412 COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci) = astArr;
4413 COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(ci) = std;
4414
4415 /* Set the OPT2 field in the ID AST to point to the COLLAPSE
4416 * structure. */
4417 A_OPT2P(astArr, ci);
4418 } else /* A_TKNG(ast) == TK_DEALLOCATE */ {
4419 astArr = astSrc;
4420 ci = A_OPT2G(astArr);
4421 if (!ci || COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci))
4422 continue; /* array doesn't qualify */
4423 if (COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci)) {
4424 delete_collapse(ci); /* multiple DEALLOCATEs found */
4425 continue;
4426 }
4427 COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci) = std;
4428 }
4429 }
4430}
4431
4432/* Delete COLLAPSE table entry #ci. */
4433static void
4434delete_collapse(int ci)
4435{
4436 COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci) = TRUE;
4437}
4438
4439/* Find the loops containing definitions of arrays within the COLLAPSE
4440 * table. */
4441static void
4442find_collapse_defs(void)
4443{
4444 int def;
4445 int nme;
4446 int ci;
4447 int lpDef;
4448
4449 for (ci = 1; ci < collapse.avail; ci++) {
4450 if (COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci))
4451 continue;
4452 if (!COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(ci) || !COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci)) {
4453 delete_collapse(ci);
4454 continue;
4455 }
4456 nme = A_NMEG(COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci));
4457 for (def = NME_DEF(nme); def; def = DEF_NEXT(def)) {
4458 if (DEF_STD(def) == COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(ci) ||
4459 DEF_STD(def) == COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci))
4460 continue;
4461 lpDef = FG_LOOP(DEF_FG(def));
4462 if (LP_CALLFG(lpDef)) {
4463 delete_collapse(ci);
4464 break;
4465 }
4466 if (COLLAPSE_LP(ci)) {
4467 if (lpDef != COLLAPSE_LP(ci) || DEF_LHS(def) != COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci)) {
4468 /* array assigned in multiple loops or
4469 * different assignments in the same loop */
4470 delete_collapse(ci);
4471 break;
4472 }
4473 } else {
4474 COLLAPSE_LP(ci) = lpDef;
4475 COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci) = DEF_ADDR(def);
4476 }
4477 }
4478 }
4479}
4480
4481/* Determine if uses of arrays in the COLLAPSE table are within the same
4482 * loops in which they are defined. */
4483static void
4484find_collapse_uses(void)
4485{
4486 int ci;
4487 int astArr;
4488 int nme;
4489 int def;
4490 DU *du;
4491 int use;
4492
4493 for (ci = 1; ci < collapse.avail; ci++) {
4494 if (COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci))
4495 continue;
4496 astArr = COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci);
4497 if (A_TYPEG(astArr) == A_SUBSCR)
4498 astArr = A_LOPG(astArr);
4499 assert(A_TYPEG(astArr) == A_ID, "find_collapse_uses: unknown array type",
4500 ci, 4);
4501 nme = A_NMEG(astArr);
4502 for (def = NME_DEF(nme); def; def = DEF_NEXT(def)) {
4503 if (DEF_STD(def) == COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(ci) ||
4504 DEF_STD(def) == COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci))
4505 continue;
4506 for (du = DEF_DU(def); du; du = du->next) {
4507 use = du->use;
4508 if (is_parent_loop(COLLAPSE_LP(ci), FG_LOOP(USE_FG(use))) &&
4509 COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci) == USE_ADDR(use))
4510 continue;
4511 delete_collapse(ci);
4512 goto next_ci;
4513 }
4514 }
4515 next_ci:;
4516 }
4517}
4518
4519/* Return TRUE if lpParent is a parent loop of loop lp. */
4520static LOGICAL
4521is_parent_loop(int lpParent, int lp)
4522{
4523 if (lpParent == 0)
4524 return TRUE; /* all loops are descendents of loop #0 */
4525 for (; lp; lp = LP_PARENT(lp))
4526 if (lp == lpParent)
4527 return TRUE;
4528 return FALSE;
4529}
4530
4531/* Replace collapsible arrays with scalars in all loops within loop lp. */
4532static void
4533collapse_loops(void)
4534{
4535 int std;
4536 int ast, astArr;
4537 int ci;
4538 int nme;
4539 int def;
4540 DU *du;
4541 int use;
4542
4543 for (ci = 1; ci < collapse.avail; ci++) {
4544 if (COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci))
4545 continue;
4546 astArr = COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci);
4547 if (A_TYPEG(astArr) == A_SUBSCR)
4548 astArr = A_LOPG(astArr);
4549 assert(A_TYPEG(astArr) == A_ID, "collapse_loops: unknown array type", ci,
4550 4);
4551 nme = A_NMEG(astArr);
4552 for (def = NME_DEF(nme); def; def = DEF_NEXT(def)) {
4553 if (DEF_STD(def) == COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(ci) ||
4554 DEF_STD(def) == COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci))
4555 continue;
4556 ast_visit(1, 1);
4557 ast_replace(COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci), COLLAPSE_ASTSCLR(ci));
4558 std = DEF_STD(def);
4559 ast = ast_rewrite(STD_AST(std));
4560 STD_AST(std) = ast;
4561 A_STDP(ast, std);
4562 ast_unvisit();
4563 for (du = DEF_DU(def); du; du = du->next) {
4564 ast_visit(1, 1);
4565 use = du->use;
4566 ast_replace(COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci), COLLAPSE_ASTSCLR(ci));
4567 std = USE_STD(use);
4568 ast = ast_rewrite(STD_AST(std));
4569 STD_AST(std) = ast;
4570 A_STDP(ast, std);
4571 ast_unvisit();
4572 }
4573 }
4574 }
4575}
4576
4577static int global_astArrdsc, global_flag;
4578
4579static void
4580look_for_descriptor(int ast, int *unused)
4581{
4582 if (ast == global_astArrdsc)
4583 global_flag = 1;
4584} /* look_for_descriptor */
4585
4586/* Set the COLLAPSE_DESCR flag to TRUE for all arrays for which a descriptor
4587 * appears within the program. */
4588static void
4589find_descrs(void)
4590{
4591 int ci;
4592 int astArr, astArrdsc, ast;
4593 int sptrArr, sptrArrdsc;
4594 int std, stdend;
4595 int nargs, arg;
4596 int args;
4597 int src;
4598
4599 for (ci = 1; ci < collapse.avail; ci++) {
4600 if (COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci))
4601 continue;
4602 astArr = A_LOPG(COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci));
4603 sptrArr = A_SPTRG(astArr);
4604 if (NODESCG(sptrArr))
4605 continue;
4606 sptrArrdsc = DESCRG(sptrArr);
4607 astArrdsc = mk_id(sptrArrdsc);
4608 global_astArrdsc = astArrdsc;
4609 global_flag = 0;
4610
4611 /* Search through STDs for an occurrence of astArrdsc in a CALL. */
4612 stdend = STD_NEXT(COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci));
4613 ast_visit(1, 1);
4614 for (std = COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(ci); global_flag == 0 && std != stdend;
4615 std = STD_NEXT(std)) {
4616 ast = STD_AST(std);
4617 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_CALL) {
4618 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
4619 args = A_ARGSG(ast);
4620 for (arg = 0; arg < nargs; arg++) {
4621 if (ARGT_ARG(args, arg) == astArrdsc) {
4622 global_flag = 1;
4623 break;
4624 }
4625 }
4626 } else if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ASN) {
4627 src = A_SRCG(ast);
4628 if (A_TYPEG(src) == A_SUBSCR) {
4629 if (A_LOPG(src) == astArrdsc) {
4630 global_flag = 1;
4631 }
4632 }
4633 } else if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_IFTHEN) {
4634 /* descriptor might be used by 'gen_single' */
4635 ast_traverse(ast, NULL, look_for_descriptor, NULL);
4636 }
4637 }
4638 if (global_flag)
4639 COLLAPSE_DESCR(ci) = TRUE;
4640 ast_unvisit();
4641 }
4642}
4643
4644/* If bDescr is FALSE, remove ALLOCATE/DEALLOCATE statements of
4645 * collapsed arrays without array descriptors. If bDescr is TRUE
4646 * delete ALLOCATE/DEALLOCATE statements of collapsed arrays with
4647 * array descriptors. */
4648static void
4649collapse_allocates(LOGICAL bDescr)
4650{
4651 int ci;
4652
4653 for (ci = 1; ci < collapse.avail; ci++) {
4654 if (COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci) || bDescr != COLLAPSE_DESCR(ci))
4655 continue;
4656 delete_stmt(COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(ci));
4657 delete_stmt(COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci));
4658 }
4659}
4660
4661static void
4662report_collapse(int lp)
4663{
4664 int ci;
4665 int lpi;
4666 int std;
4667 int lineno;
4668
4669 for (ci = 1; ci < collapse.avail; ci++)
4670 if (!COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci) && COLLAPSE_LP(ci) == lp)
4671 break;
4672 if (ci < collapse.avail) {
4673 for (std = FG_STDFIRST(LP_HEAD(lp)); std; std = STD_PREV(std))
4674 if (STD_LINENO(std))
4675 break;
4676 lineno = (std ? STD_LINENO(std) : 1);
4677 ccff_info(MSGOPT, "OPT044", gbl.findex, lineno,
4678 "Temp arrays collapsed to scalars", NULL);
4679 }
4680
4681 for (lpi = LP_CHILD(lp); lpi; lpi = LP_SIBLING(lpi))
4682 report_collapse(lpi);
4683}
4684
4685#if DEBUG
4686#ifdef FLANG_OUTCONV_UNUSED
4687/* Dump the COLLAPSE table. */
4688static void
4689dump_collapse(void)
4690{
4691 int ci;
4692
4693 for (ci = 1; ci < collapse.avail; ci++) {
4694 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "Entry %d:\n", ci);
4695 if (COLLAPSE_DELETE(ci)) {
4696 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " DELETED\n");
4697 continue;
4698 }
4699 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " Temp array: ");
4700 dbg_print_ast(COLLAPSE_ASTARR(ci), gbl.dbgfil);
4701 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " Allocate STD %d, Deallocate STD %d, Defining loop "
4702 "%d, Descriptor %d:1\n",
4703 COLLAPSE_STDALLOC(ci), COLLAPSE_STDDEALLOC(ci), COLLAPSE_LP(ci),
4704 COLLAPSE_DESCR(ci));
4705 if (!COLLAPSE_ASTSCLR(ci))
4706 continue;
4707 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, " New scalar: ");
4708 dbg_print_ast(COLLAPSE_ASTSCLR(ci), gbl.dbgfil);
4709 }
4710}
4711#endif
4712#endif
4713
4714/* END OF ARRAY COLLAPSING */
4715
4716static int
4717position_finder(int forall, int ast)
4718{
4719 int list1, listp;
4720 int isptr;
4721 int i;
4722 int reverse[7];
4723 int n;
4724 int pos;
4725
4726 n = 0;
4727 list1 = A_LISTG(forall);
4728 for (listp = list1; listp != 0; listp = ASTLI_NEXT(listp)) {
4729 reverse[n] = ASTLI_SPTR(listp);
4730 n++;
4731 }
4732
4733 pos = n;
4734 for (i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4735 isptr = reverse[i];
4736 if (!contains_ast(ast, mk_id(isptr)))
4737 pos = pos - 1;
4738 else
4739 break;
4740 }
4741
4742 return pos;
4743}
4744
4745static void
4746find_calls_pos(int std, int forall, int must_pos)
4747{
4748 int ast, ast1;
4749 int std1;
4750 int pos, pos1;
4751 int nd, nd1;
4752 int i;
4753
4754 ast = STD_AST(std);
4755 nd = A_OPT1G(ast);
4756 assert(nd, "find_calls_pos: something is wrong", ast, 3);
4757 pos = position_finder(forall, ast);
4758 if (must_pos > pos)
4759 pos = must_pos;
4760 for (i = 0; i < FT_CALL_NCALL(nd); i++) {
4761 std1 = glist(FT_CALL_CALL(nd), i);
4762 ast1 = STD_AST(std1);
4763 nd1 = A_OPT1G(ast1);
4764 assert(nd1, "find_calls_pos: something is wrong", ast1, 3);
4765 find_calls_pos(std1, forall, must_pos);
4766 pos1 = FT_CALL_POS(nd1);
4767 if (pos1 > pos)
4768 pos = pos1;
4769 }
4770 FT_CALL_POS(nd) = pos;
4771}
4772
4773static void
4774find_mask_calls_pos(int forall)
4775{
4776 int nd;
4777 int i;
4778 int cstd;
4779
4780 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4781 for (i = 0; i < FT_NMCALL(nd); i++) {
4782 cstd = glist(FT_MCALL(nd), i);
4783 find_calls_pos(cstd, forall, 0);
4784 }
4785}
4786
4787static void
4788find_stmt_calls_pos(int forall, int mask_pos)
4789{
4790 int nd;
4791 int cstd;
4792 int i;
4793
4794 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4795 for (i = 0; i < FT_NSCALL(nd); i++) {
4796 cstd = glist(FT_SCALL(nd), i);
4797 find_calls_pos(cstd, forall, mask_pos);
4798 }
4799}
4800
4801static int
4802find_max_of_mask_calls_pos(int forall)
4803{
4804
4805 int nd, nd1;
4806 int i;
4807 int cstd;
4808 int ast;
4809 int max;
4810 int pos;
4811
4812 max = 0;
4813 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4814 for (i = 0; i < FT_NMCALL(nd); i++) {
4815 cstd = glist(FT_MCALL(nd), i);
4816 ast = STD_AST(cstd);
4817 nd1 = A_OPT1G(ast);
4818 assert(nd1, "find_calls_pos: something is wrong", ast, 3);
4819 pos = FT_CALL_POS(nd1);
4820 if (pos > max)
4821 max = pos;
4822 }
4823 return max;
4824}
4825
4826static void
4827put_calls(int pos, int std, int stdnext)
4828{
4829 int ast, ast1;
4830 int std1;
4831 int pos1;
4832 int nd, nd1;
4833 int i;
4834
4835 ast = STD_AST(std);
4836 nd = A_OPT1G(ast);
4837 assert(nd, "put_calls: something is wrong", ast, 3);
4838 for (i = 0; i < FT_CALL_NCALL(nd); i++) {
4839 std1 = glist(FT_CALL_CALL(nd), i);
4840 ast1 = STD_AST(std1);
4841 nd1 = A_OPT1G(ast1);
4842 assert(nd1, "put_calls: something is wrong", ast1, 3);
4843 put_calls(pos, std1, stdnext);
4844 }
4845 pos1 = FT_CALL_POS(nd);
4846 if (pos == pos1) {
4847 delete_stmt(std);
4848 std = add_stmt_before(ast, stdnext);
4849 pure_gbl.local_mode = 1;
4850 transform_call(std, ast);
4851 pure_gbl.local_mode = 0;
4852 }
4853}
4854
4855static void
4856add_mask_calls(int pos, int forall, int stdnext)
4857{
4858 int nd;
4859 int cstd;
4860 int i;
4861
4862 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4863 for (i = 0; i < FT_NMCALL(nd); i++) {
4864 cstd = glist(FT_MCALL(nd), i);
4865 put_calls(pos, cstd, stdnext);
4866 }
4867}
4868
4869static void
4870add_stmt_calls(int pos, int forall, int stdnext)
4871{
4872 int nd;
4873 int cstd;
4874 int i;
4875
4876 nd = A_OPT1G(forall);
4877 for (i = 0; i < FT_NSCALL(nd); i++) {
4878 cstd = glist(FT_SCALL(nd), i);
4879 put_calls(pos, cstd, stdnext);
4880 }
4881}
4882
4883/* To enter local mode:
4884 * pghpf_saved_local_mode = pghpf_local_mode
4885 * pghpf_local_mode = 1
4886 */
4887void
4888enter_local_mode(int std)
4889{
4890 int ast, dest, src;
4891 int sptr = getsymbol("pghpf_local_mode");
4892 int sptr1 = getsymbol("pghpf_saved_local_mode");
4893
4894 STYPEP(sptr1, ST_VAR);
4895 DTYPEP(sptr1, DT_INT);
4896 DCLDP(sptr1, 1);
4897 SCP(sptr1, SC_LOCAL);
4898
4899 ast = mk_stmt(A_ASN, DT_INT);
4900 dest = mk_id(sptr1);
4901 A_DESTP(ast, dest);
4902 src = mk_id(sptr);
4903 A_SRCP(ast, src);
4904 add_stmt_before(ast, std);
4905
4906 ast = mk_stmt(A_ASN, DT_INT);
4907 A_DESTP(ast, src);
4908 A_SRCP(ast, astb.i1);
4909 add_stmt_before(ast, std);
4910}
4911
4912/* To exit local mode:
4913 * pghpf_local_mode = pghpf_saved_local_mode
4914 */
4915void
4916exit_local_mode(int std)
4917{
4918 int ast, dest, src;
4919 int sptr = getsymbol("pghpf_local_mode");
4920 int sptr1 = getsymbol("pghpf_saved_local_mode");
4921
4922 STYPEP(sptr1, ST_VAR);
4923 DTYPEP(sptr1, DT_INT);
4924 DCLDP(sptr1, 1);
4925 SCP(sptr1, SC_LOCAL);
4926
4927 ast = mk_stmt(A_ASN, DT_INT);
4928 dest = mk_id(sptr);
4929 A_DESTP(ast, dest);
4930 src = mk_id(sptr1);
4931 A_SRCP(ast, src);
4932 add_stmt_before(ast, std);
4933}
4934
4935static void
4936search_pure_function(int stdfirst, int stdlast)
4937{
4938 int std;
4939 int expr, newexpr;
4940 int ast;
4941 int lhs;
4942 int std1, ast1;
4943 int cnt;
4944
4945 for (std = stdfirst; std != stdlast; std = STD_NEXT(std)) {
4946 ast = STD_AST(std);
4947 /* must be forall mask */
4948 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_IFTHEN) {
4949 /* find endif */
4950 cnt = 0;
4951 for (std1 = STD_NEXT(std); std1 != stdlast; std1 = STD_NEXT(std1)) {
4952 ast1 = STD_AST(std1);
4953 if (A_TYPEG(ast1) == A_IFTHEN)
4954 cnt++;
4955 if (A_TYPEG(ast1) == A_ENDIF) {
4956 if (cnt == 0)
4957 break;
4958 else
4959 cnt--;
4960 }
4961 }
4962 expr = A_IFEXPRG(ast);
4963 newexpr = transform_pure_function(expr, std);
4964 A_IFEXPRP(ast, newexpr);
4965 }
4966 /* must be forall asn */
4967 else if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_ASN) {
4968 lhs = A_DESTG(ast);
4969 if (A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_SUBSCR) {
4970 expr = A_SRCG(ast);
4971 newexpr = transform_pure_function(expr, std);
4972 A_SRCP(ast, newexpr);
4973 }
4974 }
4975 }
4976}
4977
4978static int
4979transform_pure_function(int expr, int std)
4980{
4981
4982 int l, r, d, o;
4983 int i, nargs, argt;
4984 int newexpr;
4985
4986 if (expr == 0)
4987 return expr;
4988 switch (A_TYPEG(expr)) {
4989 /* expressions */
4990 case A_BINOP:
4991 o = A_OPTYPEG(expr);
4992 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
4993 l = transform_pure_function(A_LOPG(expr), std);
4994 r = transform_pure_function(A_ROPG(expr), std);
4995 return mk_binop(o, l, r, d);
4996 case A_UNOP:
4997 o = A_OPTYPEG(expr);
4998 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
4999 l = transform_pure_function(A_LOPG(expr), std);
5000 return mk_unop(o, l, d);
5001 case A_CONV:
5002 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
5003 l = transform_pure_function(A_LOPG(expr), std);
5004 return mk_convert(l, d);
5005 case A_PAREN:
5006 d = A_DTYPEG(expr);
5007 l = transform_pure_function(A_LOPG(expr), std);
5008 return mk_paren(l, d);
5009 case A_MEM:
5010 l = transform_pure_function(A_PARENTG(expr), std);
5011 r = A_MEMG(expr);
5012 d = A_DTYPEG(r);
5013 return mk_member(l, r, d);
5014 case A_SUBSTR:
5015 return expr;
5016 case A_INTR:
5017 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(expr);
5018 argt = A_ARGSG(expr);
5019 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
5020 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) = transform_pure_function(ARGT_ARG(argt, i), std);
5021 }
5022 newexpr = mk_func_node((int)A_TYPEG(expr), A_LOPG(expr), nargs, argt);
5023 A_OPTYPEP(newexpr, A_OPTYPEG(expr));
5024 A_SHAPEP(newexpr, A_SHAPEG(expr));
5025 A_DTYPEP(newexpr, A_DTYPEG(expr));
5026 return newexpr;
5027 case A_FUNC:
5028 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(expr);
5029 argt = A_ARGSG(expr);
5030 for (i = 0; i < nargs; ++i) {
5031 ARGT_ARG(argt, i) = transform_pure_function(ARGT_ARG(argt, i), std);
5032 }
5033 newexpr = mk_func_node((int)A_TYPEG(expr), A_LOPG(expr), nargs, argt);
5034 A_SHAPEP(newexpr, A_SHAPEG(expr));
5035 A_DTYPEP(newexpr, A_DTYPEG(expr));
5036 transform_call(std, newexpr);
5037 return newexpr;
5038 case A_CNST:
5039 case A_CMPLXC:
5040 case A_ID:
5041 case A_SUBSCR:
5042 return expr;
5043 default:
5044 interr("transform_pure_function: unknown expression", expr, 2);
5045 return expr;
5046 }
5047}
5048
5049/*
5050 * return +1 at local mode exit, -1 at local mode entry
5051 * local mode exit is 'pghpf_local_mode = saved_pghpf_local_mode'
5052 * local mode entry is 'pghpf_local_mode = 1'
5053 */
5054static LOGICAL
5055at_local_mode(int ast)
5056{
5057 int sptr = getsymbol("pghpf_local_mode");
5058 int mkid = mk_id(sptr);
5059 if (A_DESTG(ast) == mkid) {
5060 int src = A_SRCG(ast);
5061 if (src == astb.i1) {
5062 return -1;
5063 } else {
5064 return +1;
5065 }
5066 }
5067 return 0;
5068} /* at_local_mode */
5069
5070/*
5071 * eliminate barrier statements that are followed immediately by another
5072 * barrier statement.
5073 * also, eliminate barrier statements inside a 'private' mode loop.
5074 */
5075static void
5076eliminate_barrier(void)
5077{
5078 int std, stdPrev;
5079 int ast, bLocal, at;
5080 LOGICAL bFound;
5081
5082 bFound = FALSE;
5083 bLocal = 0;
5084 for (std = STD_LAST; std; std = stdPrev) {
5085 stdPrev = STD_PREV(std);
5086 ast = STD_AST(std);
5087 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
5088 case A_BARRIER:
5089 if (bLocal) {
5090 /* eliminate all barrier statements in local region, */
5091 delete_stmt(std);
5092 } else if (!bFound) {
5093 bFound = TRUE;
5094 } else if (!STD_LABEL(std)) {
5095 delete_stmt(std);
5096 }
5097 break;
5098 case A_CONTINUE:
5099 /* eliminate useless CONTINUE statements */
5100 if (!STD_LABEL(std)) {
5101 delete_stmt(std);
5102 }
5103 break;
5104 case A_ASN:
5105 /* see if we are at the bottom or
5106 * top of a pghpf_local_mode region */
5107 at = at_local_mode(ast);
5108 bLocal += at;
5109 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
5110 default:
5111 bFound = FALSE;
5112 break;
5113 }
5114 }
5115}
5116
5117static LOGICAL
5118use_offset(int sptr)
5119{
5120 LOGICAL retval;
5121 int dtype;
5122 retval = FALSE;
5123 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED || ALLOCG(sptr) || LNRZDG(sptr)) {
5124 int dty;
5125 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
5126 dty = DTYG(dtype);
5127 if (NO_PTR || (NO_CHARPTR && dty == TY_CHAR) ||
5128 (NO_DERIVEDPTR && dty == TY_DERIVED)) {
5129 retval = TRUE;
5130 }
5131 }
5132 return retval;
5133} /* use_offset */
5134
5135static LOGICAL
5136needs_linearization(int sptr)
5137{
5138 LOGICAL retval, alloc;
5139 int dtype;
5140 retval = FALSE;
5141 alloc = FALSE;
5142 if (F90POINTERG(sptr))
5143 return FALSE;
5144 if (ALLOCG(sptr)) {
5145 alloc = TRUE;
5146 } else if (F77OUTPUT) {
5147 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
5148 if ((DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY && (ADD_DEFER(dtype) || ADD_NOBOUNDS(dtype))) ||
5149 ALIGNG(sptr)) {
5150 alloc = TRUE;
5151 }
5152 }
5153 if (LNRZDG(sptr)) {
5154 retval = TRUE;
5155 } else if (F77OUTPUT) {
5156 if (alloc || use_offset(sptr)) {
5157 retval = TRUE;
5158 }
5159 } else if (alloc && (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED || STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER) &&
5160 (MDALLOCG(sptr) || PTROFFG(sptr))) {
5161 retval = TRUE;
5162 }
5163 return retval;
5164} /* needs_linearization */
5165
5166static LOGICAL linearize_any;
5167
5168static void
5169_linearize(int ast, int *dummy)
5170{
5171 /* At an A_SUBSCR? Should it be linearized? */
5172 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR && A_SHAPEG(ast) == 0) {
5173 int lop, sptr;
5174
5175 lop = A_LOPG(ast);
5176 if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_ID) {
5177 sptr = A_SPTRG(lop);
5178 } else if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_MEM) {
5179 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(lop));
5180 } else {
5181 return;
5182 }
5183
5184 if (needs_linearization(sptr)) {
5185 /* replace the subscript by the linearized subscripts */
5186 int asd, ndim, sdsc, ss, subscr[1], dtype, eldtype, newast;
5187 lop = ast_rewrite(lop);
5188 linearize_any = TRUE;
5189 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
5190 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
5191 sdsc = SDSCG(sptr);
5192 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
5193 eldtype = DDTG(dtype);
5194 if (sdsc && !NODESCG(sptr)) {
5195 int i, simple;
5196 if (!POINTERG(sptr) && SCG(sptr) != SC_DUMMY) {
5197 simple = 1;
5198 } else {
5199 simple = 0;
5200 }
5201 ss = check_member(lop, get_xbase(sdsc));
5202 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
5203 int s, stride;
5204 s = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
5205 s = ast_rewrite(s);
5206 if (XBIT(58, 0x22) && !POINTERG(sptr)) {
5207 int lw;
5208 lw = ADD_LWAST(dtype, i);
5209 if (lw) {
5210 lw = ast_rewrite(lw);
5211 lw = mk_binop(OP_SUB, lw, astb.i1, DT_INT);
5212 s = mk_binop(OP_SUB, s, lw, DT_INT);
5213 }
5214 }
5215 if (i > 0 || !simple) {
5216 stride = check_member(lop, get_local_multiplier(sdsc, i));
5217 s = mk_binop(OP_MUL, s, stride, DT_INT);
5218 }
5219
5220 if (ss == 0) {
5221 ss = s;
5222 } else {
5223 ss = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ss, s, DT_INT);
5224 }
5225 }
5226 } else {
5227 int dsym, ddtype, i;
5228 dsym = DESCRG(sptr);
5229 if (dsym) {
5230 ddtype = DTYPEG(dsym);
5231 if (DTY(ddtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
5232 dtype = ddtype;
5233 }
5234 }
5235 ss = 0;
5236 for (i = ndim; i > 0; --i) {
5237 int s, lw;
5238 lw = ADD_LWAST(dtype, i - 1);
5239 lw = ast_rewrite(lw);
5240 if (lw == 0) {
5241 lw = astb.i1;
5242 }
5243 if (i < ndim && ss != 0) {
5244 int up, stride;
5245 up = ADD_UPAST(dtype, i - 1);
5246 if (up == 0) {
5247 up = astb.i1;
5248 } else {
5249 up = ast_rewrite(up);
5250 }
5251 if (up == lw) {
5252 stride = astb.i1;
5253 } else if (lw == astb.i1) {
5254 stride = up;
5255 } else {
5256 stride = mk_binop(OP_SUB, up, lw, DT_INT);
5257 stride = mk_binop(OP_ADD, stride, astb.i1, DT_INT);
5258 }
5259 if (stride != astb.i1) {
5260 ss = mk_binop(OP_MUL, ss, stride, DT_INT);
5261 }
5262 }
5263 s = ASD_SUBS(asd, i - 1);
5264 s = ast_rewrite(s);
5265 if (ss == 0) {
5266 ss = s;
5267 } else {
5268 ss = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ss, s, DT_INT);
5269 }
5270 if (lw != astb.i0) {
5271 ss = mk_binop(OP_SUB, ss, lw, DT_INT);
5272 }
5273 }
5274 ss = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ss, astb.i1, DT_INT);
5275 }
5276 if (use_offset(sptr)) {
5277 /* add in the offset variable */
5278 int off;
5279 if ((STYPEG(sptr) != ST_MEMBER || POINTERG(sptr)) && PTROFFG(sptr)) {
5280 off = check_member(lop, mk_id(PTROFFG(sptr)));
5281 } else if (MIDNUMG(sptr)) {
5282 off = check_member(lop, mk_id(MIDNUMG(sptr)));
5283 } else {
5284 off = astb.i1;
5285 }
5286 ss = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ss, off, DT_INT);
5287 ss = mk_binop(OP_SUB, ss, astb.i1, DT_INT);
5288 }
5289 subscr[0] = ss;
5290 newast = mk_subscr(lop, subscr, 1, eldtype);
5291 ast_replace(ast, newast);
5292 }
5293 } else if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_INTR) {
5294 int arg0, argcnt, argt, argtnew, i, diff, parent;
5295 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
5296 case I_LBOUND:
5297 case I_UBOUND:
5298 case I_SIZE:
5299 case I_ALLOCATED:
5300 /* leave first argument as is, take the second argument */
5301 argt = A_ARGSG(ast);
5302 arg0 = ARGT_ARG(argt, 0);
5303 if (A_TYPEG(arg0) == A_MEM) {
5304 parent = ast_rewrite(A_PARENTG(arg0));
5305 diff = 0;
5306 if (parent != A_PARENTG(arg0)) {
5307 arg0 = mk_member(parent, A_MEMG(arg0), A_DTYPEG(arg0));
5308 ++diff;
5309 }
5310 }
5311 argcnt = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
5312 argtnew = mk_argt(argcnt);
5313 ARGT_ARG(argtnew, 0) = arg0;
5314 for (i = 1; i < argcnt; ++i) {
5315 ARGT_ARG(argtnew, i) = ast_rewrite(ARGT_ARG(argt, i));
5316 if (ARGT_ARG(argtnew, i) != ARGT_ARG(argt, i))
5317 ++diff;
5318 }
5319 if (!diff) {
5320 unmk_argt(argcnt);
5321 ast_replace(ast, ast);
5322 } else {
5323 int newast;
5324 newast = mk_func_node(A_TYPEG(ast), A_LOPG(ast), argcnt, argtnew);
5325 A_OPTYPEP(newast, A_OPTYPEG(ast));
5326 A_SHAPEP(newast, A_SHAPEG(ast));
5327 A_DTYPEP(newast, A_DTYPEG(ast));
5328 ast_replace(ast, newast);
5329 }
5330 break;
5331 }
5332 }
5333} /* _linearize */
5334
5335static void
5336_linearize_all(int ast)
5337{
5338 int dummy = 0;
5339 ast_traverse(ast, NULL, _linearize, &dummy);
5340} /* _linearize_all */
5341
5342static void
5343_linearize_sub(int ast)
5344{
5345 int lop, asd, i;
5346 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
5347 case A_ID:
5348 break;
5349 case A_SUBSCR:
5350 /* look at subscripts, look at parent */
5351 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
5352 for (i = 0; i < ASD_NDIM(asd); ++i) {
5353 _linearize_all(ASD_SUBS(asd, i));
5354 }
5355 lop = A_LOPG(ast);
5356 if (A_TYPEG(lop) == A_MEM) {
5357 _linearize_all(A_PARENTG(lop));
5358 }
5359 break;
5360 case A_MEM:
5361 _linearize_all(A_PARENTG(ast));
5362 break;
5363 default:
5364 _linearize_all(ast);
5365 break;
5366 }
5367} /* _linearize_sub */
5368
5369static void
5370_linearize_func(int ast, int *dummy)
5371{
5372 int argcnt, args, i, dont;
5373 int paramct, dpdsc, sptr, param;
5374 dont = -1;
5375 args = A_ARGSG(ast);
5376 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
5377 case A_CALL:
5378 case A_FUNC:
5379 case A_ICALL:
5380 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
5381 case I_NULLIFY:
5382 return;
5383 case I_COPYIN:
5384 if (XBIT(57, 0x80)) {
5385 int arg2, arg4;
5386 arg2 = ARGT_ARG(args, 2);
5387 arg4 = ARGT_ARG(args, 4);
5388 if (arg2 == arg4) {
5389 dont = 4;
5390 } else if (A_TYPEG(arg2) == A_SUBSCR && A_LOPG(arg2) == arg4) {
5391 dont = 4;
5392 }
5393 }
5394 break;
5395 case I_COPYOUT:
5396 if (XBIT(57, 0x80)) {
5397 int arg0, arg1;
5398 arg0 = ARGT_ARG(args, 0);
5399 arg1 = ARGT_ARG(args, 1);
5400 if (arg0 == arg1) {
5401 dont = 0;
5402 } else if (A_TYPEG(arg1) == A_SUBSCR && A_LOPG(arg1) == arg0) {
5403 dont = 0;
5404 }
5405 }
5406 break;
5407 case I_PTR2_ASSIGN:
5408 dont = 0;
5409 break;
5410 case I_PTR_COPYIN:
5411 dont = 3;
5412 break;
5413 case I_PTR_COPYOUT:
5414 dont = 0;
5415 break;
5416 }
5417 break;
5418 case A_INTR:
5419 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
5420 case I_SIZE:
5421 case I_LBOUND:
5422 case I_UBOUND:
5423 case I_PRESENT:
5424 return;
5425 }
5426 break;
5427 default:
5428 return;
5429 }
5430 argcnt = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
5431 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(ast));
5432 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_PROC) {
5433 dpdsc = DPDSCG(sptr);
5434 paramct = PARAMCTG(sptr);
5435 } else {
5436 dpdsc = 0;
5437 paramct = 0;
5438 }
5439 for (i = 0; i < argcnt; ++i) {
5440 int arg, sptr;
5441 if (i == dont)
5442 continue;
5443 arg = ARGT_ARG(args, i);
5444 if (arg != 0) {
5445 param = 0;
5446 if (i < paramct && dpdsc) {
5447 param = aux.dpdsc_base[dpdsc + i];
5448 }
5449 switch (A_TYPEG(arg)) {
5450 case A_ID:
5451 sptr = A_SPTRG(arg);
5452 break;
5453 case A_MEM:
5454 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(arg));
5455 /* see if remove_distributed_member will fix this */
5456 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) != TY_ARRAY && /* scalar */
5457 XBIT(70, 0x08) && /*remove_distributed_member is called*/
5458 ((POINTERG(sptr) && !F90POINTERG(sptr)) || ALIGNG(sptr)))
5459 /* and will replace this with a temp */
5460 continue;
5461 break;
5462 default:
5463 continue;
5464 }
5465 if (needs_linearization(sptr) && use_offset(sptr)) {
5466 int subscr[7];
5467 if (param && POINTERG(param)) {
5468 subscr[0] = astb.i1;
5469 } else if ((STYPEG(sptr) != ST_MEMBER || POINTERG(sptr)) &&
5470 PTROFFG(sptr)) {
5471 subscr[0] = check_member(arg, mk_id(PTROFFG(sptr)));
5472 } else if (MIDNUMG(sptr)) {
5473 subscr[0] = check_member(arg, mk_id(MIDNUMG(sptr)));
5474 } else {
5475 subscr[0] = astb.i1;
5476 }
5477 ARGT_ARG(args, i) = mk_subscr(arg, subscr, 1, DDTG(DTYPEG(sptr)));
5478 }
5479 }
5480 }
5481} /* _linearize_func */
5482
5483void
5484linearize_arrays(void)
5485{
5486 int std;
5487 int dummy = 0;
5488 deferred_to_pointer();
5489 /* linearize all subscripts */
5490 for (std = STD_NEXT(0); std; std = STD_NEXT(std)) {
5491 int ast;
5492 linearize_any = FALSE;
5493 ast = STD_AST(std);
5494 ast_visit(1, 1);
5495 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
5496 case A_ALLOC:
5497 /* for ALLOCATEs, don't modify the allocate target directly */
5498 if (A_LOPG(ast) != 0) {
5499 _linearize_all(A_LOPG(ast));
5500 }
5501 if (A_DESTG(ast) != 0) {
5502 _linearize_all(A_DESTG(ast));
5503 }
5504 if (A_M3G(ast) != 0) {
5505 _linearize_all(A_M3G(ast));
5506 }
5507 if (A_STARTG(ast) != 0) {
5508 _linearize_all(A_STARTG(ast));
5509 }
5510 _linearize_sub(A_SRCG(ast));
5511 break;
5512 case A_REDIM: /* skip REDIM statements */
5513 break;
5514 default:
5515 _linearize_all(ast);
5516 break;
5517 }
5518 if (linearize_any) {
5519 ast = ast_rewrite(ast);
5520 STD_AST(std) = ast;
5521 }
5522 ast_unvisit();
5523 ast_visit(1, 1);
5524 ast_traverse(ast, NULL, _linearize_func, &dummy);
5525 ast_unvisit();
5526 }
5527} /* linearize_arrays */
5528
5529/*
5530 * head of linked list of DEFs in each STD
5531 */
5532static int *stddeflist;
5533/*
5534 * head of linked list of DEFs in each LOOP
5535 */
5536static int *loopdeflist;
5537
5538typedef struct syminfostruct {
5539 int loop, defs;
5540} syminfostruct;
5541
5542static syminfostruct *syminfo;
5543
5544static int clean;
5545static int always_executed;
5546static int chk_assign;
5547static int chk_subscr;
5548
5549/*
5550 * set clean=0 and return immediately (with TRUE value) if
5551 * we find a symbol which was modified in this loop
5552 * we find an operation that is not clean:
5553 * user function call
5554 * divide
5555 * non-integer multiply
5556 *
5557 */
5558static LOGICAL
5559_check_clean(int ast, int *pl)
5560{
5561 int l, o, sptr;
5562 int asd, i;
5563
5564 l = *pl;
5565 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
5566 case A_ID:
5567 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
5568 if (syminfo[sptr].loop == l) {
5569 /* must have been a def in this loop */
5570 clean = 0;
5571 } else if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sptr) &&
5572 syminfo[MIDNUMG(sptr)].loop == l) {
5573 /* must have been a def in this loop */
5574 clean = 0;
5575 } else if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED && !always_executed) {
5576 /* pointer may be null */
5577 clean = 0;
5578 } else if (POINTERG(sptr) && !always_executed) {
5579 /* pointer may be null */
5580 clean = 0;
5581 } else if (chk_assign && chk_subscr && !always_executed) {
5582 clean = 0;
5583 } else if (LP_CALLFG(l)) {
5584 /*
5585 * The LP_CALLFG check must be last; need to check 'sptr' as above.
5586 * if there is a call in the loop, and this is a COMMON symbol, unclean
5587 */
5588 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_CMBLK || (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED && MIDNUMG(sptr) &&
5589 SCG(MIDNUMG(sptr)) == SC_CMBLK)) {
5590 clean = 0;
5591 }
5592
5593 if (ALLOCDESCG(sptr)) {
5594 clean = 0;
5595 }
5596 }
5597 break;
5598 case A_SUBSCR:
5599 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
5600 chk_subscr = 1;
5601 for (i = 0; i < (int)ASD_NDIM(asd); i++) {
5602 ast_traverse((int)ASD_SUBS(asd, i), _check_clean, NULL, pl);
5603 if (clean == 0)
5604 break;
5605 }
5606 chk_subscr = 0;
5607 break;
5608 case A_BINOP:
5609 o = A_OPTYPEG(ast);
5610 if (o == OP_DIV) {
5611 clean = 0;
5612 } else if (o == OP_MUL) {
5613 int d;
5614 d = A_DTYPEG(ast);
5615 if (!DT_ISINT(d)) {
5616 clean = 0;
5617 }
5618 }
5619 break;
5620 case A_FUNC:
5621 case A_CALL:
5622 clean = 0;
5623 break;
5624 case A_INTR:
5625 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
5626 case I_RAN:
5627 case I_RANDOM_NUMBER:
5628 case I_RANDOM_SEED:
5629 clean = 0;
5630 break;
5631 }
5632 break;
5633 }
5634 if (clean == 0)
5635 return TRUE;
5636 return FALSE;
5637} /* _check_clean */
5638
5639/*
5640 * float a statement out of a loop
5641 */
5642static void
5643sfloat_stmt(int std, int fg, int l)
5644{
5645 int next, prev, head, prehead;
5646#if DEBUG
5647 if (DBGBIT(43, 0x800)) {
5648 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "FLOAT std:%d out of fnode:%d in loop:%d\n", std, fg,
5649 l);
5650 }
5651#endif
5652
5653 /* remove stmt from std list */
5654 next = STD_NEXT(std);
5655 prev = STD_PREV(std);
5656
5657 STD_PREV(next) = prev;
5658 STD_NEXT(prev) = next;
5659
5660 /* remove stmt from fg's statement list */
5661 if (std == FG_STDFIRST(fg)) {
5662 if (std != FG_STDLAST(fg)) {
5663 FG_STDFIRST(fg) = next;
5664 } else {
5665 /* we've moved the only statement out */
5666 FG_STDFIRST(fg) = 0;
5667 FG_STDLAST(fg) = 0;
5668 }
5669 } else if (std == FG_STDLAST(fg)) {
5670 FG_STDLAST(fg) = prev;
5671 }
5672
5673 /* find FG node into which to insert the statement */
5674 head = LP_HEAD(l);
5675 prehead = FG_LPREV(head);
5676 STD_FG(std) = prehead;
5677
5678 if (FG_STDFIRST(prehead) == 0) {
5679 FG_STDFIRST(prehead) = std;
5680 }
5681 FG_STDLAST(prehead) = std;
5682
5683 do {
5684 /* should iterate only once, DO is the top of the loop */
5685 next = FG_STDFIRST(head);
5686 head = FG_LNEXT(head);
5687 } while (next == 0);
5688
5689 prev = STD_PREV(next);
5690 STD_NEXT(prev) = std;
5691 STD_PREV(next) = std;
5692 STD_NEXT(std) = next;
5693 STD_PREV(std) = prev;
5694} /* sfloat_stmt */
5695
5696/*
5697 * move a statement out of a loop downward
5698 *
5699 */
5700static void
5701sdrop_stmt(int std, int fg, int l)
5702{
5703 int next, prev;
5704#if DEBUG
5705 if (DBGBIT(43, 0x800)) {
5706 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "DROP2 std:%d out of fnode:%d in loop:%d\n", std, fg,
5707 l);
5708 }
5709#endif
5710
5711 /* remove stmt from std list */
5712 next = STD_NEXT(std);
5713 prev = STD_PREV(std);
5714
5715 STD_PREV(next) = prev;
5716 STD_NEXT(prev) = next;
5717
5718 /* remove stmt from fg's statement list */
5719 if (std == FG_STDFIRST(fg)) {
5720 if (std != FG_STDLAST(fg)) {
5721 FG_STDFIRST(fg) = next;
5722 } else {
5723 /* we've moved the only statement out */
5724 FG_STDFIRST(fg) = 0;
