5725 FG_STDLAST(fg) = 0;
5726 }
5727 }
5728 if (std == FG_STDLAST(fg)) {
5729 FG_STDLAST(fg) = prev;
5730 }
5731
5732 STD_NEXT(std) = 0;
5733 STD_PREV(std) = 0;
5734 /* put new std at the end of the list */
5735 if (LP_DSTDF(l)) {
5736 int tstd = LP_DSTDF(l);
5737 while (STD_NEXT(tstd)) {
5738 tstd = STD_NEXT(tstd);
5739 }
5740 STD_NEXT(tstd) = std;
5741 STD_PREV(std) = tstd;
5742
5743 } else {
5744 LP_DSTDF(l) = std;
5745 }
5746}
5747
5748static void
5749sfloat_stmt2(int std, int fg, int l)
5750{
5751 int next, prev;
5752#if DEBUG
5753 if (DBGBIT(43, 0x800)) {
5754 fprintf(gbl.dbgfil, "FLOAT2 std:%d out of fnode:%d in loop:%d\n", std, fg,
5755 l);
5756 }
5757#endif
5758
5759 /* remove stmt from std list */
5760 next = STD_NEXT(std);
5761 prev = STD_PREV(std);
5762
5763 STD_PREV(next) = prev;
5764 STD_NEXT(prev) = next;
5765
5766 /* remove stmt from fg's statement list */
5767 if (std == FG_STDFIRST(fg)) {
5768 if (std != FG_STDLAST(fg)) {
5769 FG_STDFIRST(fg) = next;
5770 } else {
5771 /* we've moved the only statement out */
5772 FG_STDFIRST(fg) = 0;
5773 FG_STDLAST(fg) = 0;
5774 }
5775 } else if (std == FG_STDLAST(fg)) {
5776 FG_STDLAST(fg) = prev;
5777 }
5778 STD_NEXT(std) = 0;
5779 STD_PREV(std) = 0;
5780 /* append new std at the end of the list */
5781 if (LP_HSTDF(l)) {
5782 int tstd = LP_HSTDF(l);
5783 while (STD_NEXT(tstd)) {
5784 tstd = STD_NEXT(tstd);
5785 }
5786 STD_NEXT(tstd) = std;
5787 STD_PREV(std) = tstd;
5788 } else {
5789 LP_HSTDF(l) = std;
5790 }
5791}
5792
5793void
5794hoist_stmt(int std, int fg, int l)
5795{
5796 if (STD_VISIT(std))
5797 return;
5798 /* don't do multiple exits not yet */
5799 if (LP_MEXITS(l))
5800 return;
5801
5802 STD_VISIT(std) = 1;
5803
5804 if (is_dealloc_std(std))
5805 sdrop_stmt(std, STD_FG(std), l);
5806 else
5807 sfloat_stmt2(std, STD_FG(std), l);
5808}
5809
5810void
5811restore_hoist_stmt(int lp)
5812{
5813 int next, prev, tail, head, laststd, posttail, prehead, tstd;
5814
5815 int std = LP_HSTDF(lp);
5816 if (std) {
5817 laststd = std;
5818 STD_VISIT(std) = 0;
5819 while (STD_NEXT(laststd)) {
5820 laststd = STD_NEXT(laststd);
5821 STD_VISIT(laststd) = 0;
5822 }
5823 /* find FG node into which to insert the statement */
5824 head = LP_HEAD(lp);
5825 prehead = FG_LPREV(head);
5826 STD_FG(std) = prehead;
5827
5828 if (FG_STDFIRST(prehead) == 0) {
5829 FG_STDFIRST(prehead) = std;
5830 }
5831 FG_STDLAST(prehead) = laststd;
5832
5833 do {
5834 /* should iterate only once, DO is the top of the loop */
5835 next = FG_STDFIRST(head);
5836 head = FG_LNEXT(head);
5837 } while (next == 0);
5838
5839 prev = STD_PREV(next);
5840 STD_NEXT(prev) = std;
5841 STD_PREV(next) = laststd;
5842 STD_NEXT(laststd) = next;
5843 STD_PREV(std) = prev;
5844 }
5845
5846 std = LP_DSTDF(lp);
5847 if (std) {
5848 STD_VISIT(std) = 0;
5849 laststd = std;
5850 while (STD_NEXT(laststd)) {
5851 laststd = STD_NEXT(laststd);
5852 }
5853
5854 /* find FG node into which to insert the statement */
5855 tail = LP_TAIL(lp);
5856 posttail = FG_LNEXT(tail);
5857 next = FG_STDFIRST(posttail);
5858 while (next == 0) {
5859 posttail = FG_LNEXT(posttail);
5860 next = FG_STDFIRST(posttail);
5861 }
5862
5863 for (tstd = std; tstd; tstd = STD_NEXT(tstd)) {
5864 STD_FG(tstd) = posttail;
5865 STD_VISIT(tstd) = 0;
5866 }
5867
5868 prev = STD_PREV(next);
5869 STD_PREV(std) = prev;
5870 STD_NEXT(prev) = std;
5871 STD_PREV(next) = laststd;
5872 STD_NEXT(laststd) = next;
5873 }
5874}
5875
5876/*
5877 * record the def of a symbol; also, record any equivalenced defs.
5878 */
5879static void
5880add_def_syminfo(int sptr, int l)
5881{
5882 int socptr;
5883 int ss;
5884
5885 if (syminfo[sptr].loop != l) {
5886 syminfo[sptr].loop = l;
5887 syminfo[sptr].defs = 0;
5888 }
5889 ++syminfo[sptr].defs;
5890
5891 for (socptr = SOCPTRG(sptr); socptr; socptr = SOC_NEXT(socptr)) {
5892 ss = SOC_SPTR(socptr);
5893 if (syminfo[ss].loop != l) {
5894 syminfo[ss].loop = l;
5895 syminfo[ss].defs = 0;
5896 }
5897 ++syminfo[ss].defs;
5898 }
5899}
5900
5901/*
5902 * given a loop, look at the loop header node.
5903 * it should have only one non-loop predecessor, which should have only
5904 * one successor, the loop header. That node is then a valid preheader.
5905 */
5906static LOGICAL
5907have_preheader(int l)
5908{
5909 int h, n, ph, v;
5910 PSI_P pred;
5911 PSI_P succ;
5912 h = LP_HEAD(l);
5913 n = 0;
5914 ph = 0;
5915 for (pred = FG_PRED(h); pred; pred = PSI_NEXT(pred)) {
5916 v = PSI_NODE(pred);
5917 if (FG_LOOP(v) != l) {
5918 ++n;
5919 if (n > 1)
5920 return FALSE;
5921 ph = v;
5922 }
5923 }
5924 if (n != 1)
5925 return FALSE;
5926 succ = FG_SUCC(ph);
5927 if (succ == PSI_P_NULL || PSI_NEXT(succ))
5928 return FALSE;
5929 if (PSI_NODE(succ) != h)
5930 return FALSE;
5931 /* only one predecessor outside the loop, it has only one successor */
5932 return TRUE;
5933} /* have_preheader */
5934
5935/*
5936 * if 'l' is an inner loop, look at the nodes in the loop
5937 * look at assignments and section descriptor function calls in those nodes
5938 * if this is the only assignment to the LHS and the RHS is loop invariant,
5939 * (for section descriptor functions, LHS is 1st argument, RHS is other args)
5940 * then float the statement out of the loop.
5941 * if the node is not control-equivalent to the loop entry, then require
5942 * the LHS to be a compiler temp, and the RHS to be 'safe'
5943 * safe means no faults (no divides unless denominator is constant)
5944 */
5945static void
5946sfloat(int l)
5947{
5948 int lc, fg, std, ast, firstd, lastd;
5949 /* inner loops first */
5950 for (lc = LP_CHILD(l); lc; lc = LP_SIBLING(lc)) {
5951 sfloat(lc);
5952 }
5953
5954 /* count how many defs of each variable in the loop */
5955 /* look at flow graph nodes in this loop */
5956 for (fg = LP_FG(l); fg; fg = FG_NEXT(fg)) {
5957 /* look at statements in this flow graph node */
5958 int std, stdlast;
5959 stdlast = FG_STDLAST(fg);
5960 for (std = FG_STDFIRST(fg); std; std = STD_NEXT(std)) {
5961 int d;
5962 for (d = stddeflist[std]; d; d = DEF_NEXT(d)) {
5963 int nm;
5964 for (nm = DEF_NM(d); nm; nm = NME_NM(nm)) {
5965 int sptr;
5966 sptr = NME_SYM(nm);
5967 if (sptr > NOSYM) {
5968 add_def_syminfo(sptr, l);
5969 }
5970 }
5971 }
5972 if (std == stdlast)
5973 break;
5974 }
5975 }
5976 for (lc = LP_CHILD(l); lc; lc = LP_SIBLING(lc)) {
5977 int d;
5978 for (d = loopdeflist[lc]; d; d = DEF_NEXT(d)) {
5979 int nm;
5980 for (nm = DEF_NM(d); nm; nm = NME_NM(nm)) {
5981 int sptr;
5982 sptr = NME_SYM(nm);
5983 if (sptr > NOSYM) {
5984 add_def_syminfo(sptr, l);
5985 }
5986 }
5987 }
5988 }
5989
5990 /* focus on DO loops */
5991 fg = LP_HEAD(l);
5992 std = FG_STDFIRST(fg);
5993 ast = STD_AST(std);
5994 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_DO || (XBIT(70, 0x800) && have_preheader(l))) {
5995 /* look at flow graph nodes in this loop */
5996 for (fg = LP_FG(l); fg; fg = FG_NEXT(fg)) {
5997 /* look at statements in this flow graph node */
5998 int std, nextstd, stdlast;
5999 stdlast = FG_STDLAST(fg);
6000 for (std = FG_STDFIRST(fg); std; std = nextstd) {
6001 /* is this an assignment that can be floated out,
6002 * or is this a template call that can be floated out */
6003 int ast, lhs, rhs, sptr, funcast, ll, nme;
6004 nextstd = STD_NEXT(std);
6005 ast = STD_AST(std);
6006 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
6007 case A_ASN:
6008 lhs = A_DESTG(ast);
6009 rhs = A_SRCG(ast);
6010 if (A_TYPEG(lhs) != A_ID)
6011 break;
6012 sptr = A_SPTRG(lhs);
6013 if (SCG(sptr) != SC_LOCAL || (gbl.internal == 1 && LP_CALLFG(l)))
6014 break;
6015 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr) && LP_CALLFG(l))
6016 break;
6017 /*
6018 * must be unconditional or dead after the loop.
6019 * the only definition of this symbol in the loop,
6020 * free of side effects or faults,
6021 * loop-invariant RHS
6022 */
6023 nme = add_arrnme(NT_VAR, sptr, 0, (INT)0, 0, FALSE);
6024 if ((!FG_CTLEQUIV(fg) && is_live_out(nme, l)) || is_live_in(nme, l))
6025 break;
6026 if (syminfo[sptr].loop != l || syminfo[sptr].defs != 1)
6027 break;
6028 /* loop invariant, side-effect-free RHS */
6029 clean = 1;
6030 always_executed = FG_CTLEQUIV(fg);
6031 ll = l;
6032 chk_assign = 1;
6033 ast_visit(1, 1);
6034 ast_traverse(rhs, _check_clean, NULL, &ll);
6035 ast_unvisit();
6036 chk_assign = 0;
6037 if (clean) {
6038 /* move this statement to the loop preheader. */
6039 sfloat_stmt(std, fg, l);
6040 }
6041 break;
6042 case A_CALL:
6043 funcast = A_LOPG(ast);
6044 if (A_TYPEG(funcast) == A_ID &&
6045 getF90TmplSectRtn(SYMNAME(A_SPTRG(funcast)))) {
6046 int argcnt, args, i;
6047 argcnt = A_ARGCNTG(ast);
6048 args = A_ARGSG(ast);
6049 lhs = ARGT_ARG(args, 0);
6050 if (A_TYPEG(lhs) != A_ID)
6051 break;
6052 sptr = A_SPTRG(lhs);
6053 if (SCG(sptr) != SC_LOCAL || (gbl.internal == 1 && LP_CALLFG(l)))
6054 break;
6055 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sptr) && LP_CALLFG(l))
6056 break;
6057 /* must be unconditional or a compiler temp array for which this
6058 * is a section descriptor,
6059 * the only definition of this descriptor in the loop,
6060 * free of side effects or faults,
6061 * loop-invariant arguments
6062 */
6063 nme = add_arrnme(NT_VAR, sptr, 0, (INT)0, 0, FALSE);
6064 if (!FG_CTLEQUIV(fg) && (is_live_out(nme, l) || is_live_in(nme, l)))
6065 /*if( PUREG(sptr) && !FG_CTLEQUIV(fg) )*/
6066 break;
6067 if (syminfo[sptr].loop != l || syminfo[sptr].defs != 1)
6068 break;
6069 clean = 1;
6070 ll = l;
6071 /*always_executed = FG_CTLEQUIV(fg);*/
6072 /* for now, just assume calls are always executed;
6073 * other checks for side-effects are sufficient ...?
6074 */
6075 always_executed = 1;
6076 ast_visit(1, 1);
6077 for (i = 1; clean && i < argcnt; ++i) {
6078 rhs = ARGT_ARG(args, i);
6079 ast_traverse(rhs, _check_clean, NULL, &ll);
6080 }
6081 ast_unvisit();
6082 if (clean) {
6083 /* move this statement to the loop preheader. */
6084 sfloat_stmt(std, fg, l);
6085 }
6086 }
6087 break;
6088 }
6089 if (std == stdlast)
6090 break;
6091 }
6092 }
6093 }
6094
6095 /* put the DEFs from the statements in the loop
6096 * onto the list of DEFs for this loop */
6097 /* look at flow graph nodes in this loop */
6098 firstd = 0;
6099 lastd = 0;
6100 for (fg = LP_FG(l); fg; fg = FG_NEXT(fg)) {
6101 /* look at statements in this flow graph node */
6102 int std;
6103 for (std = FG_STDFIRST(fg); std; std = STD_NEXT(std)) {
6104 int d;
6105 d = stddeflist[std];
6106 if (d) {
6107 if (firstd == 0) {
6108 firstd = d;
6109 } else {
6110 DEF_NEXT(lastd) = d;
6111 }
6112 for (; d; d = DEF_NEXT(d)) {
6113 lastd = d;
6114 }
6115 /* here, lastd points to the end of the list */
6116 stddeflist[std] = 0; /* no vestigial pointers */
6117 }
6118 if (std == FG_STDLAST(fg))
6119 break;
6120 }
6121 }
6122 for (lc = LP_CHILD(l); lc; lc = LP_SIBLING(lc)) {
6123 int d;
6124 d = loopdeflist[lc];
6125 if (d) {
6126 if (firstd == 0) {
6127 firstd = d;
6128 } else {
6129 DEF_NEXT(lastd) = d;
6130 }
6131 for (; d; d = DEF_NEXT(d)) {
6132 lastd = d;
6133 }
6134 /* here, lastd points to the end of the list */
6135 loopdeflist[lc] = 0; /* no vestigial pointers */
6136 }
6137 }
6138 loopdeflist[l] = firstd;
6139} /* sfloat */
6140
6141/*
6142 * look for section descriptor manipulations,
6143 * such as RTE_template, pghpf_sect calls,
6144 * float these out of loops if possible
6145 */
6146void
6147sectfloat(void)
6148{
6149 int savex, l, fg, nm, s;
6150 optshrd_init();
6151 induction_init();
6152 optshrd_finit();
6153 savex = flg.x[6]; /* disable flow graph changes here */
6154 flg.x[6] |= 0x80000000;
6155 /* build the flowgraph for the function */
6156 flowgraph();
6157 postdominators();
6158 /* build the loop data structure */
6159 findlooptopsort();
6160 reorderloops();
6161 /* do flow analysis on the loops */
6162 flow();
6163
6164 /* find control-equivalent nodes in loops */
6165 for (fg = 1; fg < opt.num_nodes; ++fg) {
6166 l = FG_LOOP(fg);
6167 if (l) {
6168 int head;
6169 head = LP_HEAD(l);
6170 if (fg == head) {
6171 /* this IS the loop head */
6172 FG_CTLEQUIV(fg) = 1;
6173 } else {
6174 int dom;
6175 dom = FG_DOM(fg);
6176 if (dom && FG_LOOP(dom) == l && FG_CTLEQUIV(dom) &&
6177 FG_PDOM(dom) == fg) {
6178 /* simple case, control equivalent to a control equivalent node */
6179 FG_CTLEQUIV(fg) = 1;
6180 } else if (is_dominator(head, fg) && is_post_dominator(fg, head)) {
6181 /* harder case; see if LP_HEAD dominates this node and this
6182 * node post-dominates LP_HEAD */
6183 FG_CTLEQUIV(fg) = 1;
6184 }
6185 }
6186 }
6187 }
6188
6189#if DEBUG
6190 if (DBGBIT(56, 2)) {
6191 dumpfgraph();
6192 dumploops();
6193 dumpnmes();
6194 dumpdefs();
6195 dumpuses();
6196 }
6197#endif
6198 /* unlink DEF_NEXT list from NME, link into a list based on STD */
6199 NEW(stddeflist, int, astb.std.stg_size);
6200 BZERO(stddeflist, int, astb.std.stg_size);
6201 NEW(loopdeflist, int, opt.nloops + 1);
6202 BZERO(loopdeflist, int, opt.nloops + 1);
6203 NEW(syminfo, syminfostruct, stb.stg_avail);
6204 BZERO(syminfo, syminfostruct, stb.stg_avail);
6205 for (nm = 1; nm < nmeb.stg_avail; ++nm) {
6206 int d, nextd;
6207 for (d = NME_DEF(nm); d; d = nextd) {
6208 int std;
6209 nextd = DEF_NEXT(d);
6210 std = DEF_STD(d);
6211 DEF_NEXT(d) = stddeflist[std];
6212 stddeflist[std] = d;
6213 }
6214 }
6215 /* mark those section descriptor arrays that are
6216 * section descriptors for user symbols */
6217 for (s = stb.firstusym; s < stb.stg_avail; ++s) {
6218 switch (STYPEG(s)) {
6219 case ST_ARRAY:
6220 case ST_DESCRIPTOR:
6221 case ST_STRUCT:
6222 case ST_MEMBER:
6223 if (!CCSYMG(s) && !HCCSYMG(s)) {
6224 int sdsc;
6225 sdsc = SDSCG(s);
6226 if (sdsc) {
6227 PUREP(sdsc, 1);
6228 }
6229 }
6230 break;
6231 default:;
6232 }
6233 }
6234 for (l = LP_CHILD(0); l; l = LP_SIBLING(l)) {
6235 sfloat(l);
6236 }
6237
6238 FREE(syminfo);
6239 FREE(loopdeflist);
6240 FREE(stddeflist);
6241 optshrd_fend();
6242 induction_end();
6243 optshrd_end();
6244 flg.x[6] = savex; /* disable flow graph changes here */
6245} /* sectfloat */
